title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Put on stove and let boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and then oatmeal while mixture boils.
Add vanilla.
Stir to dropping consistency.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: sizzling sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly. Mix in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and serve immediately over warm rice, sprinkling with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cooking time is 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburg chop suey
directions: Braise hamburg.
Add soy sauce, salt and bouillon.
Add onion and chop suey vegetables.
Cover and cook until boiling.
Blend cornstarch, ginger, molasses and water.
Add and stir until thickened.
About 4 servings.

title: pineapple diamonds
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch with a little water and cook until thick for spreading.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Boil lobsters in water for 18 minutes.
Cut in half and break off claws.
Remove meat from shells and set half shells aside for stuffing.
Cut lobster into 1-inch pieces.
Brown shallots or onions in butter, then add white wine and let boil until reduced. Slowly stir in half and half and white sauce.
Add salt, cayenne, white pepper and chervil.
Simmer until mixture coats a spoon.
Add lobster and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from fire and add moistened mustard and 3/4 of the cheese.
Fill shells with mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Glaze in hot oven or under broiler for 1 minute until golden brown.
Garnish and serve 4.

title: oven steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Brown steak on both sides in melted shortening.
Place browned steak in a large pan.
Add onion soup mix and cover with water.
Place aluminum foil over pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until steak is tender.

title: scalloped eggplant and onions
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Boil until tender and drain.
Peel onions.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Parboil 5 minutes.
Drain well and saute in butter until tender, but not browned.

title: crumb cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar and melted margarine.
Put aside 3/4 cup of crumbs.
To remaining crumbs, add eggs, milk and soda.
Divide into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Add a little cinnamon to remaining crumbs and sprinkle over cakes.
Bake at 365° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes (enough to fill up a large Pyrex dish) and set aside.
Slice bacon up in one inch pieces and saute with onions until bacon is crisp.
Dump potatoes into giant mixing bowl.
Dump in bacon, onions plus bacon drippings.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and 2 cups milk.
Mix well.
Dump into large Pyrex bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Poke 2 holes in top of plastic.
Cook on High for 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: "my mom's potato dish"
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool them and peel, then shred the potatoes.
Melt margarine and mix in with potatoes.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; fold in sour cream.
(Mix in.)
Put in baking dish and top with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: blondies
directions: Cream all sugar and butter together.
Add eggs 1 at a time. Mix in flour and stir well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook, cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: frozen punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until completely clear and hot enough to melt the Jell-O.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve Jell-O.
Cool.
Add juices, extract and water.
Mix well.
Stir some during freezing. Remove from freezer 6 hours before serving. Serves 50 generously. (I freeze in Tupperware cake box or square keeper.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Mix in egg and vanilla flavor.
Blend in flour mixture and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet (lightly greased).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour to layer pans. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Beat 5 min, on high. Blend flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately with water and vanilla. Mix on low. Pour into pans. Bake about 35 min. Cool. Split each layer crosswise into two layers. (You will have a 4 layered cake.) Spread whipped topping or sweetened whipped cream between layers. Frost with Brown Beauty Icing. Cake will keep 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: homemade play doh
directions: Cook all ingredients 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and let cool until it is comfortable to handle. Store in container with tight lid.

title: aunt florence's delicious zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion until tender; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and grated carrots.
Fold into zucchini and onion mixture; set aside.
Melt margarine and add the seasoning packet from the stuffing mix; mix well.
Fold into the stuffing.
Place half of the dressing in the bottom of a long casserole pan.
Add the vegetable mixture and place the remaining dressing mixture over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar; add gelatin which has been softened in the water.
Stir until melted.
Add lemon juice and cherry juice.
Cool.
Mash cream cheese and add cherries.
Mix with pineapple and chill until slightly thickened.
Whip the whipping cream and blend with pineapple mixture.
Mold and chill.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg yolks (one at a time), baking soda, water, flour, sour cream and bananas.
Stir in chocolate chips. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(Time depends on your oven. Check at 1 hour.)
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Salt, pepper, & flour meat.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
Add onions & cook until soft; then add 3 or 4 cups water & cook until tender.
Add soup & cook 5 minutes longer.
Add sour cream.
Cook noodles & drain.
Then pour into meat mixture.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender (do not overcook).
Drain well after rinsing with cold water.
Allow to cool.

title: chocolate chip-cream cheese squares
directions: Cut rolls in thin slices and lay on bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press slices together until it covers bottom.
Cream the cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together and spread on top of cookie mix.
Place slices of second cookie roll on top (just place, they spread as they bake).
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool, refrigerate and cut.

title: sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and honey.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir flour, spices and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add oatmeal and mix well. Add raisins or dates and 1 cup chopped nuts if desired.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen, depending on size you like. Store in airtight container and they will stay chewy.

title: parsleyed carrots
directions: Husk and silk corn.
Wrap each ear in waxed paper; twist ends of paper.
Arrange corn on paper toweling; allow at least 1 inch between ears.
Microcook one ear about 2 minutes, two ears 3 to 4 minutes, four ears 6 to 7 minutes and six ears 8 to 10 minutes. Halfway through cooking, rearrange corn and turn over.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Cook sausage until about half done.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes; cool. Put about 1 spoonful on each biscuit.
Add Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Can add thin slice of pepperoni. Bake approximately 10 minutes at 400°.
If desired, for freezing, cook without the cheese, freeze on cookie sheet and later transfer to plastic bags.
Flaky biscuits are to be split apart; four pizzas to a biscuit.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Cook
potatoes.
Drain	and
mash
with
old
fashioned potato masher
(not
mixer).
Leave
lumpy.
Cut cooked eggs. Keep
2 eggs for the top of the dish.
Add mayonnaise (as much as you prefer) and onions and fold into potatoes.	If you have fresh bacon
fat,
add
3 teaspoons.
Add 1 teaspoon mustard. Slice reserved eggs over top of salad and enjoy.

title: delicious and nutritious cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Put oats and boiling water in a bowl; let stand.
Combine sugars, oil and eggs well.
Stir in oatmeal; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together; add to oatmeal mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread in prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done. Remove from pan.
Immediately spread prepared frosting onto the cake.

title: chicken tidbits
directions: Cut breasts into narrow strips about 1/2 inch; dip in buttermilk and then into seasoned flour; fry
in deep fat.

title: queen of puddings
directions: Melt butter in milk; stir it into the bread crumbs in a bowl. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and leave mixture to soak for 30 minutes. Stir the egg yolks into the soaked mixture.
Pour into a 5-cup ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until just set.

title: cran-banana cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Mix water, bouillon cubes, potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook for additional 10 minutes.
Add cheese and soups.
Let cheese melt.
Serve with cornbread.

title: double layer pumpkin pie(rich and creamy)
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread onto bottom of crust. (Helpful hint: Soften cream cheese in the microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds.)

title: quiche squares
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle chopped green peppers in bottom of dish.
Grate sharp Cheddar over peppers.
Beat eggs until good and frothy and pour over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: italian beef and vegetables
directions: Thinly slice the meat into bite-size strips.
Preheat a 10-inch micro-browning dish.
Add meat; cook, uncovered, until meat is done.
Set aside.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler over boiling water. Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Continue to stir while adding evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring occasionally.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart. Great for gift giving.

title: peach melba cobbler
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk, beating well with each addition.
Portion about 7 cups batter into each spray-coated steam table pan.
Portion 3 cups berries over batter. Portion 3 cups peaches over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before serving.
Cut each pan into 24 servings.
Serves 100.

title: hummus dip
directions: Toast sesame seed in small skillet over low heat.
In a blender, puree sesame seed, garlic, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup oil until smooth.
Add chickpeas alternately with lemon juice and remaining oil.
Stir in parsley, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with toasted pita bread triangles.

title: tomato relish
directions: Put all ingredients into a large kettle.
Simmer until reduced to 1/2 (2 to 3 hours) on low heat.
Pour into pint jars.
Seal with lids and process for 20 minutes in water bath canner.
Makes 6 pints.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Thaw and chop the artichokes.
In a large skillet, cook the artichokes in the oil over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add the Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese and stir the eggs in the mixture.
Season with salt.
Line an 8-inch pan with 1 sheet of puff pastry.
Pour the mixture into the pastry case.
Cover with the remaining sheet of puff pastry.
Seal and trim the edges. Bake the pie in a preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until the pastry begins to brown.

title: corned beef seashell macaroni casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleomargarine until transparent but not brown. Add seasonings, tomato paste, water and corned beef. Cook sauce until thick, but not dry.
Boil macaroni until tender. Drain and add to sauce, mixing well. Top with cheese and let melt.

title: cathedral candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in heavy saucepan; remove from heat and stir in eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture onto foil-covered cookie sheet.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Roll mixture into jelly roll shape.
Chill until chocolate is hard (approximately 6 hours).

title: health salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; fold into the vegetable mixture.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: *Be careful not to add salt until you taste the liquid to determine what salt the seasoning meat produces.

title: steward rabbit
directions: Clean rabbit and boil rabbit in water with salt, pepper and onion until meat comes off bone.

title: alphabet pretzels
directions: Dissolve water and yeast.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat egg lightly with 1 tablespoon water.
With a large spoon, work flour mixture into yeast mixture in a large bowl.
When about 3 cups of flour have been worked in, begin to knead the mixture on a countertop, while working in the remaining mix.
Divide the dough into 18 to 24 parts.
Shape the dough into letters and place on greased pans.
"Paint" with egg-water mixture and sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown at 425°.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Prepare and cook carrots. Cut into lengthwise strips.
Cook and stir brown sugar, salt and orange peel in margarine in 12-inch skillet until bubbly. Add carrots.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed and heated, about 5 minutes.

title: stuffed frankfurters
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise; don't cut all way through.
Top with sauerkraut.
Season with caraway seeds.
Top with mashed potatoes; sprinkle each with shredded Cheddar.
Bake in baking pan in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Mince onion.
Mix all well.
Best if made the day before.

title: den's baked dove kabobs
directions: Filet dove breasts, slice bell pepper, mushrooms, tomatoes, jalapenos and bacon.
Place alternating pieces of dove and the other ingredients on a toothpick.
Arrange kabobs in a large Pyrex baking dish.
Add broth and sliced onion on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs and pineapple. Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of brown sugar on top of cake. Place in oven at 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook ground beef.
Season to taste.
Drain peas and mash with potato masher until thick paste.
Add to ground beef.
Stir well. This is your filling.
Your kids will not recognize the peas. Wrap in egg roll skins.
(There are directions on the package.) Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter in pan.
Drizzle remaining batter on top.
Bake at 325° until done (45 to 60 minutes).
Mix the confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla; pour over cake while still hot.
Punch holes in cake with fork for sauce to soak in.

title: savory cheese grits
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces.
Add salt to water and bring to a boil.
Slowly add grits and bring to a second boil.
Reduce heat and cook over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add cheese and butter, stirring until melted and blended. Pour into ungreased casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-sodium garlic-ginger chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
(The high temperature will caramelize the sauce on the chicken.)
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle ginger and garlic around and under chicken pieces.
Pour oil and lemon juice over chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover baking pan tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour. Remove foil.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce or reduced sodium soy sauce, if desired, and bake uncovered for an additional 15 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter/ margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk until smooth. Pour mixture into buttered pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over dough mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy chicken supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
On sheet of waxed paper, place bread crumbs.
In pie plate, beat mayonnaise and milk until smooth.
Dip chicken breasts into mayonnaise mixture, then coat with crumbs. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken in pan; bake 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over; bake 10 to 15 minutes, until juices run clear and chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 main dish servings, about 265 calories per serving.

title: popsicles
directions: Simmer annotto seed in a little water for 10 minutes.
Let stand overnight to soften seed.
Drain.
Combine seed with garlic, peppercorns, oregano and onion and grind to a fine consistency in an electric spice grinder or a mortar.
Store in a glass jar in the refrigerator.

title: dutch carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly, about 1 hour or until carrots are tender.
Serves 4.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown beef in frypan.
Season with salt, onion salt and pepper. Mix well; drain fat off.
Place a layer of cheese over beef.
Add dry noodles, then stewed tomatoes over top and water in order given.
Cover; cook over high until steam appears.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, heat oil 1 minute.
Add meat.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently to brown meat.
Add onion and garlic; microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in water, soup and mushrooms.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, covered, stirring twice.
Test beef for tenderness.
Slowly blend in sour cream; heat 1 minute.
Serve on cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach roll-up appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread mixture over tortillas and roll up like jelly roll.
Refrigerate until firm then slice into rolls.
Good for 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.

title: sausage herb bread
directions: Place butter, herbs and cheese in separate shallow bowls. Roll each dough ball on a lightly floured surface to a 1/8-inch thick circle. Coat each dough circle with butter, herbs and cheese.

title: jam squares
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (except jam) in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups of mixture.
Press remaining mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread preserves evenly on crumb base.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over jam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: grandmama's brownies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 325°.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove skin from chicken; rinse and dry.
Season and coat each piece with oil or dip in milk.
Shake; remove excess.
Roll in crumbs.
Let stand for awhile.
Place chicken in an oiled baking pan (line pan with foil for easy clean up).
Do not crowd; pieces should not touch.
Bake for 45 minutes or more.
Crumbs will form a crisp "skin."
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Chop all vegetables and add Salad Supreme.
Mix all ingredients and add Italian dressing.
Will keep in the refrigerator for approximately two weeks.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in heavy skillet, add 3/4 cup water. Cook until like molasses.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks well, add to rest of ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook until boiling, add carmelized sugar.
Cook until thick, add vanilla.
Cool; when mixture is cool pour into cool baked shell. Top with meringue.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimentos; mix well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in bowl.
Melt chocolate on stove, then add all ingredients.
Stir well, then drop by spoon on wax paper.
Let cool until hard, about 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla together, then add baking soda, salt, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and walnuts. Gradually add flour to make the consistency of oatmeal.
(You may not need all 3 cups of flour.)
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 40 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
You can use a Bundt pan, then bake for 1 hour.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and pepper; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon salt. Mix and let stand 1 hour. Squeeze and drain. Bring to boil remaining ingredients. After liquid is cool, pour over vegetables. Put in box and freeze.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift first four (dry) ingredients together.
Cream shortening, eggs and sugar, then add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.	Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken livers with spinach, mushrooms and cheddar cheese
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in medium size saucepan.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour, mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
(Keep warm.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger. Add onion and cook thoroughly.
Drain off excess grease. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. This freezes well.

title: sunday best green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until soft. Add crumbled bacon, beans, cheese and mushrooms.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts.
Place mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 20 minutes.
May be made day before and reheated. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts (microwave or otherwise).
Cook broccoli. Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated Cheddar cheese, lemon juice and seasonings. Drain broccoli and arrange in bottom of flat greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Remove skin and bone from chicken.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Thaw the berries.
Drain the pineapple and save the juice. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and pineapple.
Slice the bananas and put in the saved juice; set aside.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Soften the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups boiling water, oats, molasses, shortening and salt.
Cool a few minutes.
Stir in 2 cups flour; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in yeast; beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Mix until smooth.
Grease top lightly.
Cover and put in refrigerator 2 hours.
Turn out on well floured surface; shape into 2 loaves. Place in greased pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix jello into strawberries to dissolve.
Stir in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: In small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup oleo; mix well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: crunchy potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow to chill.
Then serve on lettuce leaves or salad greens.

title: rosemary dinner rolls
directions: In medium saucepan, heat milk over low heat to lukewarm (105° to 110°). Transfer to a large bowl. Stir in sugar, salt and 4 tablespoons margarine. Stir in yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and rosemary. Gradually add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Add up to 1 cup more flour if needed until dough is no longer sticky.

title: barbecue
directions: In saucepan, mix vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper, cayenne, lemon juice, onion and butter.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Add meat to your desired consistency; more meat, less juicy or less meat, more juice!
Serve on rolls/bread.

title: rose's excellent stuffed mushrooms
directions: Blend together equal amounts of cream cheese, sour cream and whipped marshmallow.
Great for sliced apples and oranges.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Place mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture, then sprinkle with nuts.
Drizzle 1 1/2 cups butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 or more.
May top with whipped topping or cream.
Also may want to add a little more spices, if desired.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: goldilocks pasta and fagioli
directions: In a saucepan fry the garlic gently in the olive oil until golden brown.
Add the tomato sauce and water and cook 10 minutes. Add the beans, stir gently and continue to cook on simmer until the beans are heated through.
Cook macaroni as package directs, drain and add to bean mixture.
Stir gently to combine.
If it gets too thick, add a little more water.
Add parsley to taste. Serve with grated cheese.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add sugar, butter and milk. Stir until mixture comes to a boil. Boil mixture 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add marshmallows and peanut butter. Stir until melts. Keep stirring until thick enough to pour into buttered dish.

title: eggplant with corned beef
directions: Slice eggplant diagonally in 3/4-inch thick pieces with two slits.
Saute eggplant and onion in vegetable oil until limp.
Add corned beef.
Season with sugar and shoyu according to taste.
A quick and easy meal, great with rice.

title: miss daisy's cranberry salad
directions: Stir jello in boiling water.
Add cranberries and crushed pineapple with juice.
Let jell; freezes well.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients and juice.
Mix well.
Add cherries and nuts. Bake in foil-lined or greased pans at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.

title: purple jubilee dessert pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fresh fruit glaze
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.
Pour over fresh fruit of any kind and serve.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti, eggs, 1/2 cup Parmesan and oleo. Place into 10-inch pie plate and shape into a crust shape. Spread cottage cheese on crust.
Add meat sauce on top of cottage cheese.
On top of meat sauce, place Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan on top.
Place in 350° oven for half hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook soups and cheese together until cheese melts.
Watch and stir this frequently to prevent burning. Spread meat in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes or until Tater Tots are crisp on top.

title: better homes & gardens perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With mixer, beat pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, spices, and salt.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: In medium skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic.
Add 1 1/4 cups milk and cream cheese. Cook and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add a little of this mixture to the beaten egg; return to mixture in skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in cooked broccoli; set aside.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with 1/2 the pastry. Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese into slices and arrange on top of mixture.
Adjust the top crust of the meat pie.
Seal.
Use fork to make perforations in the pie crust. Brush top with a little milk.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Melt shortening in heavy pan.
Arrange in the following order: onion, potatoes, ground beef, rice, celery and beans.
Combine seasonings in liquids and pour over stew.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Makes 1 1/4 cups or the equivalent of 1 can.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix ingredients and put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until done, remove chicken and put noodles in the water.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain, then add mushroom soup, chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Then add chicken, stir together and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and pour over casserole. Then melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place cubed bread in 9-inch square casserole.
Combine cheese, margarine, mushrooms and ham.
Sprinkle over bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: five hour stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Do not peek while cooking.
Cut ingredients to suit your taste, any size.
Mix gently all ingredients in a casserole dish and cover.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix these by hand. Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes. Cool 30 minutes in the pan before removing.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Cut angel food cake into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on 9 x 9-inch dish.
Layer creamed mixture, Cool Whip and cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour batter over nuts/coconut mixture in pan.
Melt oleo and cream cheese; blend in powdered sugar; pour over cake mix and spread evenly.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350°
oven.
Allow to cool completely before cutting.
Cake will crack as it cools.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls (meatball size).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(You can freeze them unbaked.)

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful into deep hot oil. Hush puppies will turn themselves when underside is brown.
Cook until golden brown on all sides.
May take more or less to make stiff batter.

title: salmon fresca(yield: 2 servings)
directions: 1. Heat oven to 425° or grill to medium-high.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine margarine, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until margarine melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas and brown rice(new years)
directions: Cook peas, onion, ham and garlic together for 10 or 15 minutes.
Whisk vinegar and jalapeno pepper together and add the oil slowly in a stream and whisk until mixed.
Add oil mixture to the pea mixture.
Stir in the lemon juice and green onions; salt and pepper.
Marinate for at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally. (This will keep for many days refrigerated.)

title: cheddar cheese snacks
directions: Heat oleo, red pepper, salt and flour.
Add cheese and Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Press with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Layer bacon and rice in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine dry soup mix, soup and water in bowl; mix well.
Pour half the mixture over rice.
Arrange chicken over rice. Layer mushrooms and remaining soup mixture on top.
Sprinkle with pimento.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine
in a medium saucepan; add flour and milk.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Add eggs, green pepper, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Chop cabbage, tomatoes and peppers together.
Add corn and beans.
Pack into quart jars.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and 1 teaspoon vinegar per quart jar.
Fill with cold water.
Seal and store in cool place.
Makes 17 to 20 quarts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth and vegetables in a large pan; bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in chicken soup, chicken and pepper.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken seafood paella
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery, onion and garlic in oil in a heavy ovenproof Dutch oven until tender.
Add rice and cook until rice is straw-colored.
Add chicken broth and next 5 ingredients. Remove from heat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp, chicken and Parmesan cheese to rice mixture, stirring well.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a casserole dish, ungreased.
Mix in some Cheddar cheese and put the rest on top.
Heat in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Remove 1 1/2 cups beans and mash smooth.
Set aside.
In a large pan, in oil, cook ham, vegetables and spices until vegetables are tender and begin to brown. Add tomatoes, broth, spinach and mashed beans.
Heat to boiling, then simmer 15 minutes. Add whole beans and heat through.
Sprinkle each bowl with grated Parmesan.

title: the colonel's coleslaw(serves 8)
directions: Mix all together except cabbage.
Add to cabbage and mix well. Serve ice cold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Knead together all ingredients.
Put into bread loaf pan. Bake at 350° approximately 1 1/4 hours.
Let it brown to your liking.
You can top with catsup or barbecue sauce the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Separate the dough into eight triangles.
Place a sausage on wide end of each triangle and roll up.
Place, tip down, on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple crunchy(willie mae bridges)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Sift flour and soda together. Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour mixture, vanilla and 1 tablespoon pineapple syrup.
Stir in corn flakes.
Press into balls 1 1/4-inches in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and make an indentation in each with thumb.
Fill with crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Store uncovered.

title: unbaked corn flake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in pan and let mixture boil slightly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well. Pour into greased pan and press down.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Store in covered container.

title: spiced bread in a jar
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Spray 8 wide mouth pint jars with non stick cooking spray.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in applesauce, water and eggs.
Add mixture of flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices. Fill prepared jars 2/3 full.
Place on middle oven rack leaving as much space as possible between jars.
Bake for exactly 45 minutes. Remove jars from oven one at a time.
Seal quickly with 2 piece lids pressing bread down if necessary.
Cool.

title: easy toffee candy
directions: In medium pan melt 1/4 cup butter.
Pour into foil lined 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Arrange crackers over butter.
In same pan melt remaining butter; add sugar.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Spread over crackers.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until bubbly and slightly darkened. Remove from oven; cool 1 minute.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips; let stand 5 minutes until melted.
Spread chocolate.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press into candy.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: faye's hamburger soup
directions: Crumble hamburger and brown.
Drain.
Add tomatoes (chopped up), tomato sauce, bouillon and onions.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots and cabbage; continue cooking until tender.
Do not overcook vegetables.

title: dunking sauce(quick and easy hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Heat jelly in saucepan until melted.
Stir in mustard.
Add meat.
Simmer until heated through.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the apples, raisins and nuts.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt two times and mix with fruit and nuts.
Beat together thoroughly the brown sugar, or Sweet 'N Low, the Mapleine, eggs, Crisco oil and vanilla.
Add to apple mixture. Mixture will be hard to mix.
Do not add more liquid!
Use 9 x 12-inch pan or tube pan.
Use butter or shortening to grease pan. Heat oven to 325° and bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Diabetics should calculate fruit sugar based on serving size.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Then add rest of ingredients a little at a time and mix as you go. Pour in pan. Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze and set out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: dorothy schulte's cream cheese pie
directions: Place cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip in bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with your favorite fruit or berries.

title: beef and carrot casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and carrots.
Add to cooked noodles and mix well. Alternate layers of meat mixture and cottage cheese mixture.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole, beginning and ending with noodles. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Can be frozen and reheated at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pork tenderloin in orange sauce
directions: Saute meat in butter until golden brown.
Remove meat from pan.
Saute onion, salt and pepper in butter until onion is tender.
Return meat to skillet.
Pour wine and juice from oranges over meat.
Sprinkle sugar and parsley over; add bay leaf.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice and garnish with orange peel that has been sliced thin and boiled in small amount of water until tender.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into pineapple until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill several hours before serving.

title: potato latkes
directions: Squeeze most of water out of the grated potatoes using your hands.
Put them into a large bowl; add eggs, beaten.
Add matzo meal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add grated onion.
Heat shortening in heavy pan, fat hot but not smoking.
Drop latke batter by tablespoons; fry on both sides until crisp and brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 4.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients with 3 cups of water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and cool in refrigerator. When cooled, mix in oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: dilled zucchini
directions: Cut 2 medium zucchini lengthwise in half.
Cook, covered, in 1-inch boiling water 12 to 15 minutes, or until tender; drain. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with dill weed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jeanie's party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except sherbet.
Use as a garnish.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream egg, Crisco and butter together.
Then add molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Then roll these in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine Tang, pineapple juice, lemon juice and pudding mix together.
Stir until thick.
Fold in pineapple and oranges. Before serving, add sliced bananas to mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chops with caper sauce
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Heat butter and oil; brown chops well on each side.
Season with black pepper.
Remove chops; set aside. Add onion to skillet; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine; bring to boil.
Simmer until almost evaporated.
Stir in flour; cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Slowly stir in broth until well combined.
Add tomato and capers.
Return chops to sauce, spooning sauce over them to coat well.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: senator paul simon's "illinois pork sausage souffle"
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Put layer of bread, then sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard to eggs and pour over bread.
Top with cheese and cover with plastic wrap overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top for last 5 minutes (1 1/2 cups).

title: heavenly hamburger pie(quiche)
directions: Mix biscuit mix and cream together.
Knead on a dusted board. Roll dough.
Put into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream the eggs, butter and sugar.
Add milk and pineapple. Pour
into baking dish.
Top with bread cubes.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare according to directions on box of cake mix.
Bake.
For instant pudding:
Prepare according to directions on box.
After cake is done, crumble half of cake in punch bowl.
Add half the cherry pie filling, half the pudding, half the crushed pineapple, half the whipped cream and half the coconut.
Repeat layers.
Chill overnight.

title: healthy doggie biscuits
directions: Blend garlic, onion and water together for 2 minutes.
Add cayenne pepper and blend again.
Let mixture stand for 24 hours. Strain through cheesecloth or nylon stockings.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Spray and repeat every 2 weeks.
Will not harm animals or plants.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Combine tomatoes and tomato sauce and stew for 30 minutes. Alternate stewed mix with a few basil leaves and blend in blender. Put mix back on low heat and add heavy cream and sweet cream butter.
Flavor with cracked pepper and salt.

title: breakfast egg sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients except for muffins.
Spread mixture on bottom half of muffins and cover with top half.
May be warmed in oven.

title: candy kiss cookies
directions: Cream oleo, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls. Roll balls into sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a candy kiss firmly on top of each cookie.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: crawfish fettuccini
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in margarine until onions are translucent.
Add crawfish and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Add half and half and cheese and cook on low heat approximately 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Toss parsley into mixture, then toss mixture into cooked fettuccini noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put salt over chopped tomatoes; let stand about 3 hours. Squeeze out water and add vinegar, sugar, onions and pepper.
Stir often.
Let come to a boil (but do not boil).
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into lightly greased 2-quart pan.
Top with pastry (canned biscuits work well).
Cut slits into pastry to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes, or until crust is brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: fruit salad mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 7-Up and bananas.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add pineapple and marshmallows to Jell-O.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar and flour until thick.
Cool thoroughly. Whip whipping cream until firm and fold pineapple juice mixture into whipped cream.
Spread onto firm Jell-O.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve when cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce and fill cake pan 1/2 full. Add other ingredients in order as listed.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: harvest pie(yield: 10-12 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mexicali spoon bread casserole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, chili powder, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper and olives.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Mix milk, cornmeal and 1/2 teaspoon salt in saucepan.
Heat just to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and eggs.
Pour hot beef mixture into ungreased 3-quart casserole or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Immediately pour cornmeal mixture over top.
Cook uncovered in 375° oven until knife inserted into topping comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add persimmon pulp and beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter casserole and add melted butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: anytime muffins
directions: Combine oats and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, oil and buttermilk.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients with All-Bran just until moistened.
Store in refrigerator.

title: floating crust cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with 1 cup sugar; let stand.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt; add milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars, eggs, vanilla and Crisco until smooth.
Add flour (one cup at a time).
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.

title: black-eyed pea balls
directions: Mix peas, meat and onion well.
Add eggs and seasoning.
Then add bread crumbs until mixture sticks together and you can make into small balls.
Roll in flour and deep fry.
They will float when done.
Good for a snack or meal.

title: no cook cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip in a large bowl. Beat well; fold into pie crust.
Top with any type fruit or drip chocolate syrup.
Cool 3 hours.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Mix together in a large bowl.
Bring oil, sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat and add celery seed and mustard seed to hot mixture.
Pour mixture over slaw and do not mix, for 4 to 6 hours.
Place in refrigerator, after 4 to 6 hours, mix and serve.
Will hold in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: valarie's slaw
directions: Cut cabbage up in bite-size pieces.
Cut cheese and salami in bite-size pieces.
Combine in bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss. Excellent!

title: low sugar strawberry jam
directions: Hull
and
slice
strawberries.
Place in saucepan.
In bowl, combine
sugar
and
gelatin.
Add to strawberries; stir well to thoroughly	coat berries.
Let sit 30 minutes.
(This draws out the
juice and turns mixture vibrant red.) Bring to boil.
Remove from
heat immediately and set aside 30 minutes to cool
down. Stir.
Spoon
into	jars or other freezer containers.
Let	cool to	room temperature.
Seal and freeze or refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups jam.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and onion.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together in a ball or two long rolls.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve with party crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water until completely dissolved. Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Refrigerate to set. Serves 8.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done; peel.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon, margarine and marshmallows.
Mash with potato masher until well mixed.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix milk, flour and sugar together and pour over melted oleo. Then pour two cups sweetened peaches on top of this mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add eggs. Add flour and soda.
Mix well after each addition.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Set
oven
at
Place margarine in pan for baking and melt as oven heats.
Mix cinnamon and sugar. Remove melted margarine
from
oven. Dip biscuits on each side in margarine, then
roll	in
cinnamon-sugar mixture on each side. Return to baking pan. Sprinkle with any remaining sugar mixture and bake as directed for biscuits, approximately 12 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes, onion and celery until tender.
Add ham bone and beans (if dried beans are used, cook as usual before adding other ingredients).
Simmer for 1 hour.
Water may be added if soup is too thick.
This can be cooked in the crock-pot. Put everything in crock-pot; let cook for 5 or 6 hours.
Serve with corn bread.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
In small bowl, stir berries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients; stir until just blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: First cook hamburger; fry down, then add onion soup mix and chopped bell pepper, cooking slow (stir often), about 7 minutes. Add soup (do not dilute); simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, simmering about 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: syrian rice
directions: *Can be found in pasta section of grocery.

title: elderberry blossom tea
directions: In a tea cup or mug, steep elderberry blossoms in boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes; strain.
Add sugar and lemon.
Yield: 1 serving.

title: little smokies sausages
directions: Roll sausages around in pan of liquid smoke.
Bake at 325° (uncovered) for about 30 minutes (or until desired amount of grease is out of sausages).
Remove from liquid smoke and grease. Put in barbecue sauce before serving.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Quarter the biscuits.
Place several at a time in the bag and shake to coat. Place in round Bundt pan.
Melt butter and 1 cup sugar to a syrup. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove pan from oven and immediately flip over to allow syrup to seep through. Serve warm.
Do not slice, just pull apart.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: dean darling's pineapple-banana nut snack cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
In a large bowl, sift together flour and baking powder.
Add cinnamon, sugar and salt. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Add oil, pineapple, eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
(Do not use mixer.)
Fold into mixture the pecans and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Cook hamburger, chopped peppers and chopped onion until onions are clear.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir often.
Serves 30.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain the oranges and pineapple well.
After the fruit is drained, mix all in a large bowl together and save washing extra bowls.
Mmm Mmm Good!!
If you need more, just double the recipe.

title: seven layer cookies(anita farmer, smithfield, new york)
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs.
Spread on a layer of each of the next 4 ingredients. Pour the Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake at 320° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: aunt sissie's rolls or doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in 2 cups lukewarm water.
Add to sugar mixture with eggs.
Add flour and salt. Knead the dough, then set in warm place until doubled in bulk. Roll it thin and cut out doughnuts.
Dip in melted shortening and place on wax paper to rise for about an hour or more.
Fry in deep fat for 30 or 40 seconds on each side.
Dip in milk and confectioners sugar glaze while hot.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Melt fat in a skillet; toss in hamburger, breaking it up in small pieces.
Fry until medium brown.
Crush or chop garlic fine and mix into the meat along with salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.

title: chicken livers in patty shells
directions: Cook livers slowly in butter in covered skillet until thawed and browned, stirring often.
Add celery and onion, cook until tender.
Gradually blend in soup, milk and paprika.
Heat through, stir often.
Bake patty shells according to package directions. Serve livers in shells.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.
Very rich.

title: salmon and cucumber spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and yogurt.
Add to salmon mixture and mix to spreading consistency.
Spread on party rye bread.

title: suzie juice
directions: Pour into glass (over ice, if desired).
Can also use orange or pineapple juice instead of orange-pineapple juice.
Serves 1.

title: cowboy's supper
directions: Brown steaks with flour on them in the oil.
Drain off any excess oil.
Add potatoes, Ranch beans, butter beans and just enough water so the food won't stick.
Stir in seasonings.
Simmer in skillet until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 7 people.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces and place in large bowl.
Mix whipped topping, sour cream, evaporated milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold into cake.
Put cake mixture into large baking dish. Mix strawberries with glaze.
Put over cake mixture.
Chill several hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and form into balls and put into 2-quart casserole.
Pour can of soup over the top and bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Bake an additional 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown stuffing mix in magarine.
Spread 1/2 ounce oil in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and mushrooms; mix and blend all with chicken.
Spoon over stuffing mix in pan. Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Decorate with dried parsley. Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carnation meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pack lightly in a 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken.
Place in boiler with salt and enough water to cover.
Cook 1 hour or until tender. Cool.
Remove from bones and cut up in bite size pieces.
While chicken is cooking, make dumplings.

title: lemonade iced tea
directions: Boil water in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add tea bags. Steep for 5 minutes.
Pour tea into a pitcher and add other ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Fill the pitcher with water, then pour half into another pitcher and fill both again with water.
Chill.

title: sliced angel food cake filling
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Add pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat until thick. Add the margarine and lemon juice.
Beat egg yolk into mixture, a little at a time.
Fold in pineapple, nuts, cherries (cut up) and coconut. Spread between layers and on top of cake. Top cake with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chewy coconut bars
directions: Beat egg yolk, vanilla, shortening and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Stir in flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Pat firmly over bottom of greased and floured pan (8 or 9-inch square).
Beat egg and extra egg white.
Add vanilla and 1 cup brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Spread over other layer in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 9 to 12 bars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Drain fat.
Break bread into pieces and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sausage on top of bread.
Mix together the eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl. Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake
in
a pie crust at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil the macaroni.
Drain.
Cut cheese (1 1/2 pounds for a large amount) into cubes.
Cut cucumbers, tomatoes and onions into cubes.
Mix everything together.
Add Miracle Whip and mix.
Later on add more Miracle Whip and pepper.

title: raspberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and let stand for 24 hours.
Carve out center of bread loaf and place dip in just before serving.
Use chunks of bread and crackers for serving.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into cream mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Let sit on cookie sheet for one minute before removing.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Grease loaf pan well.

title: nut cookies
directions: Make a dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in strips.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a moderate oven for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In large bowl, break broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces; combine with onion.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, cheese, salt, basil and mayonnaise; mix well.
Toss vegetables and dressing.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add bacon, lettuce, croutons and water chestnuts; toss lightly.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet and drain off grease. While ground beef is browning, cook pasta in boiling salted water until slightly tender and drain. Add onion, pepper, spices, tomatoes, tomato sauce and drained pasta to beef mixture.
Cook for 15-20 min or until most of the liquid is absorbed. Dot with cubed cheese, Cover pan and cook for 10 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain; beat eggs and milk together.
Break bread up in baking dish; add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
May prepare the night before, then bake in the morning.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and flour in pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Alternately layer apples, cranberries and sugar mixture.
Cover with crust and bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: To each quart jar and 1/8 teaspoon alum, 1 head fresh dill or 1 teaspoon dill seed, 2 to 3 cloves of garlic, 1 teaspoon hot pepper and cucumbers.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour hot solution over cucumbers and seal.
Pickles will be ready in 3 to 4 weeks depending on the size of the cucumbers.
Recipe makes 7 quarts of brine.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir to blend.
Pour into 9 lightly oiled muffin cups. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 9 muffins.
One muffin = 121 calories, 2 g.
protein, 18 g. carbohydrate and 6 g. fat.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Process cabbage and carrot in a food processor until grated. Stir together dressing, pickle relish, and celery seeds in a large bowl; add cabbage and carrot, and toss.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: basic roll dough
directions: In a large bowl dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Beat the egg and stir in all other ingredients except add only half the flour. Add more flour until the dough is stiff enough to work with the hands.
Place a small amount of flour on table; transfer dough and knead for about 5 minutes.
Wash and grease the bowl.
Place dough in bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Push down and let stand 30 minutes.
Shape into rolls or loaf.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Grease tops with butter and serve hot.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer asparagus in dish.
Mix water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimento and eggs with mushroom soup.
Pour over asparagus.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with onion rings.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: super easy apple pie
directions: Butter a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Put apples in dish.
Lay bread slices over apples, covering apples.
Mix sugar, egg, margarine and vanilla; pour over bread.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until apples are done and crust is brown.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese as you remove pie from oven.

title: stuffing
directions: In a large bowl, tear bread into small pieces.
Add onions and celery; mix well.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients except water.
Add butter mixture to bread; mix well.
If too dry, add 1 to 2 cups water.

title: broccoli-cauli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Cut tomato into similar sized chunks.
Pour Ranch dressing over vegetables.
Stir lightly.
Use low-fat or fat free dressing for a delicious low-calorie salad!

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Melt butter and add flour, stirring until smooth; add milk, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Cook, stirring only until cheese melts.

title: squash casserole
directions: *Can also use fresh squash.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn back to 350° and bake until set.

title: cabbage soup and noodles
directions: In large pot brown beef and drain, add tomatoes, onions and carrots.
Slice cabbage thin or shred and add to pot, cook until carrots and cabbage are tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with noodles or add to soup.
"Noodles tend to sometimes take up the broth, so I put the noodles in bowl and then put soup over!"
You can make your broth weaker or stronger, however you like.

title: country kitchen chicken soup
directions: Combine noodles, flavorings and 8 cups of water in large pan. Bring to boil; cover. Simmer 30 minutes. Discard bay leaf. Stir in 3 cups cooked chicken. Simmer an additional 10 minutes.

title: "dingbats"
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook over low heat until dates and sugar dissolve.
Add nuts, cook for 10 minutes more (still on low heat, just barely bubbling).
Remove from heat, add vanilla and Rice Krispies (it will be very thick).
Immediately roll into 1-inch balls (with well-buttered hands).
Roll balls in 4x sugar. Store in airtight container.
Makes several dozen.

title: nighty nights
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff with cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar and mint flavoring.
Add green food coloring until mixture is lime green color.
Gently fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto grease-free baking sheet.
Put in oven and turn off.
Leave for 8 hours. Makes 3 dozen.

title: raggedy anne salad for two
directions: On two plates, start with the hard-cooked egg, sliced lengthwise for the face.
Next, slice the tomato in half and add to the plate.
Shred the carrot and arrange around the face of the egg for hair.
Arrange the lettuces for the skirt.
Take 3 cloves for the eyes and nose and 3 for the other plate.
Slice the celery sticks and arrange for the arms and legs.
Dab mayo for buttons on the tomato.
Under the skirt (lettuce leaf) add a cup of potato salad, macaroni salad or yogurt.
Enjoy.

title: dad's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with additional catsup.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add the condensed milk while continuing to beat until all the condensed milk is blended in.
Add the lemon juice and vanilla and blend well.
Pour into the prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before garnishing.
Before serving, top the pie with the cherry pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: thanksgiving morning bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water. Cream the butter in a very large bowl and beat in the granulated sugar
until it is no longer grainy. Add whole eggs and egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sprinkle in the salt and lemon rind. Add 4 cups of the flour.
Mix, then stir in the dissolved yeast.
Mix in 2 more cups of flour and as much of the last cup as you need to make a dough. Turn out on a floured board and knead for 7 to 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Add a little more flour if dough seems sticky.
Put dough in a buttered bowl, butter the top and cover.
Let the dough rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's cranberry salad(relish)
directions: Use grinder, blender or processor to coarsely chop cranberries.
Pour sugar over cranberries.
Dissolve Jell-O with hot water, then add cold water and chill slightly.
Chop oranges and nuts.
Mix all ingredients into Jell-O and chill several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Combine all uncooked vegetables with ground beef.
Cover in water and simmer until almost tender.
Add remaining vegetables that are precooked, including tomatoes.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: company pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put in uncooked pie crust and bake approximately 30 minutes at 325°.

title: praline bars
directions: Beat eggs and blend with sugar. Stir in butter and add flour gradually. Add vanilla and pecans. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool on rack and cut into squares. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 2 dozen.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place roast with water and garlic salt in slow cooker.
Cook on low heat overnight or until tender.
Peel and dice carrots and potatoes. Put vegetables with soup mix over roast. Cover and cook until vegetables are cooked. Serve 8 hearty eaters or 6 preachers.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and soda. Add eggs and mix well. Add pineapple with
juice and mix well again. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting or Betty Crocker frosting, which is easier.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: baby blue salad
directions: Toss greens with balsamic Vinaigrette and blue cheese.
Place on 6 plates.
Arrange orange slices over greens.
Sprinkle with berries; top with sweet and spicy pecans.
Yield 6 servings.

title: quick and easy butter pecan pie
directions: Follow directions for pudding on package.
Pour into pie crust.

(You may make a graham cracker crust and you may add bananas to pudding; this is optional and according to your taste.) Take Cool Whip and other package of dry butter pecan pudding mix and mix together.
Drain juice from pineapple and add 1/2 small can to Cool Whip mixture.
Spread on top of pudding mixture in pie crust.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook pork and beef well.
Cook onion and celery in broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Dice the cooked meat and add to the sauce. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat well.
Add eggs, Crisco, milk and flour.
Add flavoring; beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix 1 cup sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Mix well, then blend sour cream in batter.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir just enough to blend.
Put 1/2 of cinnamon mixture in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 of batter over cinnamon mixture.
Put remaining cinnamon mixture on top of batter, then add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake about 25 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: tangy carrots
directions: Cut carrots into strips and cook in slightly salted water. Reserve water they are cooked in.
Place carrots in baking dish. Combine and pour over carrots 1/2 to 2/3 cup of liquid, grated onion, horseradish and mayonnaise.
Combine and sprinkle over top butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour canned fruit together in a large bowl.
Add dry pudding mix and mix well.
Refrigerate covered.
Before serving, slice bananas and sprinkle with several tablespoons of lemon juice to keep from browning.
Add to fruit mixture.

title: cold spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Add dressing just prior to serving.

title: cheese spread
directions: Put all ingredients through the food chopper.
Blend with 1/2 cup salad dressing.
Roll up in waxed paper.
Chill overnight. Use as a spread for open faced or regular sandwiches.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion, then add all other ingredients.
Simmer together 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: sauce gumbo(okra sauce)
directions: Put oil in casserole.
Cut up onion and fry.
Separate the seeds from tomatoes.
Put in casserole and cook.
After a few minutes, put in 4 cups water, beef and okra.
Cook 1 hour or until very done.
Mash all ingredients and cook 10 minutes more.
Put in bouillon cubes and salt; cook a little.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add pecans and coconut.
Add lemon juice last.
Pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix tuna and soup together.
Season with salt and pepper. Spread on bread to make a sandwich.
Toast sandwich on both sides in the oven.

title: wassail
directions: Mix and simmer 10 minutes. Float lemon and/or orange slices.

title: scallops st. jacques
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter slowly for 5 minutes (don't brown).
Add shallot and garlic; cook 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and chili sauce.
Cook until smooth.
Add to ground beef.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain. Add taco seasoning and water; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spread beans in a 13 x 9 dish. Spread on taco meat, then taco sauce. Combine salsa and sour cream and spread over meat mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Serve at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: apple relish
directions: Cook ingredients slowly for 1/2 hour, and pack in sterile, hot jars.

title: banana bread(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over shortening in a large bowl. When melted, add sugar, cold water, salt, flour, yeast dissolved in warm water and eggs.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
(Can be kept for 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.)

title: chicken tortilla casserole(microwave)
directions: In
medium
size
bowl,
combine
soup, water and green chilies.
In 2 quart microwavable casserole, layer ingredients in this
order.
Place
tortillas in bottom, overlapping to fit. Add
can
chunk	chicken,
1/4 of the cheese and some diced pimiento.
Top
with
of
the soup mixture.
Repeat layering 2
more times, but after the last layer, top with the remaining cheese and pimientos.
Cover casserole with plastic wrap.
Vent and
microwave
on Medium for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut into wedges and serve with lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: black bottom cupcakes(or magic monday muffins)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Beat in water, then oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Line large cupcake tins with foil liners.
Fill each 2/3 full with Mixture 2.
Drop 1 tablespoon of Mixture 1 onto each cupcake.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tracey's terrific brownies
directions: Combine chips and margarine in microwave dish.
Cook on High 2 minutes; stir.
Add milk; stir.
Then add next 3 ingredients.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Mix together sugar, Karo and peanut butter.
Warm until soft. Add cornflakes.
Mix well and shape into balls.

title: pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl, combine pears, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Place top crust on pie. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Skin tomatoes and slice into 5 to 6 sections.
Dredge in the flour.
Saute in the butter or oleo.
Do not brown.
When thickened, stir in brown sugar and gradually add milk, stirring well.
Cook over low heat until thickened, then stir in salt and pepper to taste; keep stirring.
Keep warm until ready to serve over fried potatoes, mashed potatoes or biscuits.
Yummy!

title: mom's henny penny
directions: Cook chicken; remove bones and cut in bite-size pieces.
Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add corn and soup. Cook macaroni in chicken broth until tender.
Drain off any remaining broth and stir in Velveeta cheese until melted.

title: fruit coffeecake
directions: Do not drain fruit.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots diagonally and cook in salted water until tender (drain).
Cut green peppers and onions; add to drained carrots. Combine and heat soup, sugar, oil, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and vinegar; pour over carrots and let set overnight.

title: apple-raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, milk, yogurt, margarine and egg.
Let stand 5 minutes.
In a bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in bran mixture just until blended.
Next, stir in raisins and apple.
Spoon batter into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes or until done.

title: pina colada dessert dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend yogurt and pudding mix.
Stir in pineapple and extracts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: christmas wine (glogg)
directions: Heat seed, cloves, orange peel, raisins, almonds and cinnamon sticks until soft.
Add vodka and wine.
Heat until almost boiling.
Light a match over mixture and burn off excess alcohol for 5 to 10 seconds.
Add syrup to taste.
Let sit for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Bottle in glass for 2 to 3 days.
Include all ingredients when bottling.
Serve warm with cinnamon stick.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake potatoes at 425° one hour or until done.
Cool on rack until cool enough to handle.
Cut in half lengthwise and remove some potato from center. leave enough around edges so potato will hold its shape.
Brown chicken pieces in sprayed skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion, green pepper and brown. Drain excess liquid.
Add soup, sour cream, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into potato halves.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Save centers from potatoes for mashed potatoes.

title: fettucini salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and rinse in cold water in colander.
Drain again and put into salad container.
Mix other ingredients into noodles.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and add a little milk to make creamy.

title: two potato gratin
directions: Grease a shallow 4-cup ovenproof dish. Peel potatoes and sweet potato and cut into slices. Place potato and onion in prepared dish in alternating layers. Pour chicken stock over potatoes. Sprinkle evenly with cheese and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce
heat
and simmer as long as desired.
Add additional water as needed.
Mixture may be stored in refrigerator for several days and reused.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Thicken about 3 cups broth with flour and milk which have been mixed together to make a paste. Saute onions.
Add chicken, Ro-Tel (not drained), onions, garlic salt and cream of mushroom soup to broth mixture.
Bring to boil. Butter baking dish or spray with Pam.
Line 1/2 package Doritos. Add a layer of chicken mixture and layer of cheese, then add another layer of Doritos and chicken mixture, topping with cheese the last 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Place all
ingredients
in saucepan and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Strain.
