Serve hot in mugs.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; try to get out all lumps. Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix the milk and sugar.
Put the salt in milk and bring to a boil.
Add the corn meal. Stir until cooked, almost 2 minutes. Stir in the egg yolks and baking powder.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: moon rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of the coconut.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add broccoli; mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch dish at 400° for 25 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: laura's french toast with blueberry sauce
directions: Beat well first 5 ingredients. Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat. Dip 4 slices bread in mixture, coating both sides. Cook in skillet until golden brown, turning once, about 1 to 2 minutes per side. Transfer cooked slices to plate; keep warm in oven. Cook remaining slices.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into meatball size balls. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, and flour.
Then add cream of coconut, apples, and chopped pecans.
Stir well.
Then put in large pan and bake, at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls onto cookie sheets with edges together to form sheet of dough.
Bake at 375° for approximately 8 minutes. Cool.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on dough.
Add vegetables over mixture; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and cut into bars.
Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake one hour.

title: choc-oat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat the margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour and baking soda and mix.
Stir in oats and morsels and mix well. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and spread over a large cookie sheet pan and bake until light brown.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia sweet potato bake
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and slice.
Cut lemon and orange into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange sweet potatoes, lemon and orange slices in a lightly greased, shallow, 2-quart casserole.

title: paula's coconut cake
directions: Follow instructions on cake mix box. Cool cake for 15 minutes.

title: bojangles-style biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until it becomes crumbly. Add buttermilk; stir with wooden spoon.
Put on floured board; pat out with hands.
Cut with biscuit cutter, small or large.
Bake at 400° until biscuits have begun to brown.
Slip out of stove and brush quickly with margarine.
Return to oven; bake until brown enough.
Butter again if you like.
Bake at 400° on a cookie sheet.

title: flaming fruit sauce
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
In a 1-quart bowl, combine cornstarch and a little of reserved juice until smooth. Stir in remaining reserved syrup and lemon juice.
Microwave on Full power until thickened and bubbly.
Fold in fruit.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage.
Fry bacon; drain grease and mix in cooked cabbage.
Mix together vinegar and sugar and thicken with flour. Pour over cabbage and bacon and simmer until hot.

title: cranberry fizz
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add to ginger ale.
Makes 64 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in salted water with butter.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Spread broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish, then add chicken.
In separate bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in order.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs or stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: franke's tamale pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add slowly to boiling water and cook slowly, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Line bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole with cooked cornmeal.
Set aside.
Cook next 4 ingredients until meat browns, stirring often. Add next 4 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often. Put this mixture in cornmeal lined casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until
hot and bubbly.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add lemon juice; set aside.
Cool.

title: meatballs with onion sauce
directions: Mix meats, crumbs, egg and salt thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in hot fat.
Add soup, cover and simmer gently. (Or bake in 350° oven until meat is well cooked.)

title: classic company green beans
directions: Place beans in 2 quart casserole.
Cook, covered with lid, on High, 9 to 11 minutes or unitl beans are tender; stir twice.
Stir in soup and half of onion pieces; top with remaining onion pieces. Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving. Yield:
6 servings.

title: louisiana frankfurter gumbo
directions: Melt margarine in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add celery and green pepper; saute until slightly soft.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add tomatoes, frankfurters, onion, garlic and the spices.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Ladle over cooked rice in large soup bowls. Serve with French bread.
A hot, spicy dish!

title: cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Roll out 1 can of rolls into casserole dish (9 x 13 sprayed w/Pam). Mix together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, lemon juice & vanilla. spread over rolls. Spread other can of rolls on top. Brush with egg white. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into balls and brown in 1/4 cup oil.
Drain meat balls and add to sauce or gravy.

title: jane's no-knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Set aside.
Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Add oil and yeast water and the rest of the water.
Mix well with a spoon.
Place dough in a greased, covered bowl; let rest 30 minutes.

title: livingston family cornbread dressing
directions: Cook hen in large pot with salted water until tender.
You will need a lot of broth. While hen is cooking, mix up cornbread as follows:
Mix meal, flour, eggs and buttermilk well.
Add onion and celery.
Bake on 350° to 400° until browned.
Crumble white bread and put some of the broth over this.
When cornbread is done, mix with white bread.
Add more broth and mix well.
Add chopped boiled eggs and black pepper.
Be sure mixture is almost soupy.
Add deboned hen and bake on 350° until it begins to brown lightly.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Blend shortening and margarine.
Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and soda and add alternately with buttermilk. Add 1 2/3 cups coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into cake batter.
Bake in 3 layers for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost cake with icing.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and sugar. Add eggs, pineapple (with its juice) and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Cool.
Beat the cream cheese. Whip confectioners sugar and soft butter.
Spread the whipped cream cheese over the cool cake.

title: frances' molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and let cool.
Mix in order given.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Add taco seasoning mix. Follow directions on package. You can do this in a crock-pot or in oven. Mix well the refried beans, hamburger, seasoning and salsa. Put cheese on top. Heat until cheese melts.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook limas and broccoli separately until tender.
Add soup and seasonings to limas.
Put layer of broccoli; cover with limas mix. Cover with crushed Rice Chex.
Pour melted butter over all and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven in hot oil, brown salt pork, cured ham and olive oil.
Lower to medium heat.
Add and saute garlic, salt, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, olives, Sazon-Goya con pimento and cilantro and chicken bouillon for 2 minutes.
Then add chicken, browning slightly.
Add 3 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil. Continue boiling for 10 minutes.
Add rice (water should cover rice slightly).
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir (bottom to top).
Cook for another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coke cake frosting
directions: Heat coke and butter; pour over 1 box powdered sugar and other ingredients. Add vanilla and pecans. Frost cake.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend at low speed until a ball forms, about 1 minute.
Dough will be stiff. Make balls and flatten with the bottom of a glass, dipping glass in sugar for each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy. Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Save 1 1/2 cups of oat mixture.
Press remaining oat mixture on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, juice and peel at medium speed until well blended.
Pour over oat mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with rest of oat mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until lemon layer is set and bars pull away from pan.

title: flavored pretzels
directions: Melt margarine.
With whisk, combine dressing and margarine. Toss with pretzels.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool; place in sealed container. Enjoy!

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cut rolls in halves and spread half of mixture over bottom of rolls.
Put ham and cheese on top and put top of rolls on.
Spread remaining mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 3 minutes longer.
Can freeze before cooking and then cook 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix together and blend in remaining ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Mix shortening	and
sugar; mix in egg yolks. Add 1 cup milk and flour; beat well.
Pour in 3 stiff beaten egg whites. Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use icing of your choice.

title: millionaires
directions: Place caramels in 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well.
Add milk and microwave on High for 1 1/2 or 2 minutes, stirring twice.
Add pecans and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered waxed paper.
Cover and chill.
Melt paraffin in microwave.
Add chips.
Microwave on Medium until chips are soft, about 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Dip caramel pieces in chocolate and put on waxed paper until cool.

title: new england corn pudding
directions: Mix corn.
Beat in 2 eggs, flour, milk or cream.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Dot with bits of butter (amount of butter is optional).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat.
Beat eggs; add cheese, milk, mustard and salt.
Break bread into pieces or cut into cubes.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with sausage.
Pour milk-egg mixture over bread and meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix chocolate chips and marshmallow cream together in a large bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar, milk and margarine together in a large heavy saucepan.
Put on high heat until boiling fast, turn on low heat and boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over first mixture.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden. Stir in flour.
Add broth and wine.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Place a toast slice in each individual heatproof soup bowl.
Ladle soup over toast.
When toast rises to top, spoon cheese over toast.
Place in very hot oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook the celery with the nutmeg in butter until tender.
Add soup, sour cream, chicken, pineapple, nuts, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Stir now and then.
Serve in patty shells or Toast Cups.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: english muffin in a loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until very warm (120°-130°F).
Add to the dry mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon mixture into two greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pans that have been sprinkled with cornmeal after they were greased.
Sprinkle the tops with more cornmeal.
Cover, let rise in warm, draft-free place for 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from pans and cool.
To serve: Slice and toast if desired.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch square Pyrex dish, layer bottom of dish with cookies after each one has been dipped in milk.
Spread layer of Cool Whip over cookies.
Layer another layer of dipped cookies. Spread Cool Whip over cookies.
Crumble 1 cookie over Cool Whip for decoration.
Refrigerate and ready to eat in 20 to 30 minutes. Delicious!!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork. Add remaining ingredients, except blueberries. Stir until moistened. Batter will be lumpy. Add blueberries and stir. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate or grind potatoes and onions into a bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Mixture should be the consistency of pudding.
If too thin, add more flour.
Drop by large spoonfuls into hot fat about 1/2-inch deep.
Fry until crisp and golden brown, turning once.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and then add sifted flour; mix well. Spread thinly on a greased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet (with sides). Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and peanut butter together.
Pour the mixture over the cereal.
Mix and press into 9 X 13 pan.
Melt the chips together and add enough milk until creamy.
Pour over cereal mixture in pan.

title: sausage bake
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Tear bread into pieces and place in 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Cover with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, place in cold oven and turn oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.
This is delicious for a Sunday morning breakfast.

title: oatmeal superchip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have baking sheets ready.
In a large bowl with mixer on high speed, beat first 8 ingredients (butter through salt) until well blended.
Reduce speed to low; beat in flour just until blended.
Stir in oats, chocolate and pecans. Drop rounded tablespoons about 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake on baking sheet, then remove to a wire rack to cool.

title: mystery pie
directions: *One large can crushed pineapple, 3 packages of frozen peaches, 3 packages of frozen strawberries or 3 pints fresh strawberries.

title: tangy tutti fruit punch
directions: Combine lemon, pineapple, orange and maraschino cherry juice and mix well in large container.
Pour over large block of ice in punch bowl, also ginger ale.
Garnish with cherries.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Toss macaroni with vegetable oil and add celery, onion, salt and
pepper.
Add
mayonnaise and mix with diced tomato. Garnish with
parsley and thin slices of tomato.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour for more flavor.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix flour and cocoa together.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Melt butter in microwave.
Mix together cocoa, flour, eggs and sugar. Add buttermilk.
Add vanilla and pecans last.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (use unbaked pie shell).

title: acini de pepe soup
directions: In large pot, boil chicken (for flavor, add 1 carrot, 1 stalk celery and 1 onion; leave skin on).
Let cook for 1 1/2 hours. Strain into another pot.
Bone and skin chicken; add to broth. Add chopped onion, sliced carrots, chopped celery, bouillon cubes, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
You may wish to add more water to broth, depending on how much soup you wish to make.
Cook acini de pepe according to package directions.
Strain and add to finished soup.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pie crust in pan and prick sides and bottom.
Bake for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven, prick crust again and bake 3 additional minutes.
Cool.
Saute onion in margarine and remove from heat.
Add spinach and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir in spinach mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter and mix in with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pacific rim salmon cakes with mixed salad greens
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Toss with bread crumbs, onions, cilantro and ginger.
Mix in egg whites.
Form into 8 patties. Coat patties with more bread crumbs and saute them over medium heat in a small amount of oil until brown on both sides.

title: roasted garlic smashed potatoes
directions: Place garlic in small tin with enough olive oil to cover. Add sea salt.
Cover loosely with foil and roast in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

Remove foil and cook an additional 15 minutes. In a small pan, place potatoes with enough chicken stock to cover. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes; remove lid and continue cooking until stock is reduced by half and potatoes are tender.
Add garlic and pepper to potatoes in stock.
With a firm whisk, smash mixture, adding butter and half and half.
Do not use mixer.
Add salt to taste.
Mixture should be the consistency of coarse oatmeal.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine potatoes, butter and sugars.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl; stir well.
Add sweet potato mixture and buttermilk to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir all ingredients together.
Put into blender or food processor.
Blend well. Refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: orange spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 teaspoons of mixture to one cup of boiling water.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in a little of the milk.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks.
Add 1/2 cup milk and beat.
Heat milk to scalding. Add sugar.
Add eggs to cornstarch.
Add eggs and cornstarch mixture to hot milk, stirring constantly.
Take off fire and add vanilla.

title: open-face pita sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch strips.
Heat reserved 1 tablespoon oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Cook chicken, Italian seasoning and onion in oil about 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Stir in tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.

title: mozzarella cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with crackers, pretzels, chips or vegetables. For lower fat content, this tastes just as yummy with low-fat or non-fat ingredients.

title: vitality meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop onion.
Wash and chop parsley. Add beef, pork, onion and parsley to bowl.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Press firmly into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in bottom of 36 cup coffeemaker.
In basket add the spices.
Perk full cycle.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry onion in bacon drippings.
Put onion and chopped bacon bits on baked pie crust.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
together first 4 ingredients, then add milk.
Stir and cook until bubbly.	Stir in chunk of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple pandowdy(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together 1 cup flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Make a well in the center; add melted butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir together to form a rich biscuit dough.
Roll dough out to 1/4-inch thin rectangle.
Spread dough with apples, and then sprinkle with nutmeg.
Roll dough and apple sup like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch rounds.
Lay out flat in baking dish.
Mix remaining sugar, salt and flour.
Pour boiling water over sugar mixture.
Add butter and stir until butter has melted.
Pour over apple rounds and bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: pie crust cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Add flavoring.
Add liquid to dry ingredients (as you would for pie crust).
Roll and cut, not too thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Good luck!

title: pineapple mousse
directions: Place pineapple, vanilla and lemon juice in blender.
Turn on. Leave running.
Add boiling water.
Add gelatin.
Slowly pour in skim milk powder.
Pour into custard cups or pie plate and refrigerate at once. One-fourth of entire recipe equals 1 fruit and 1/4 daily milk allowance.

title: irish country soup
directions: Combine soup, peas, bouillon and milk in 1 1/2-quart microwavable container.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, until bubbly hot, stirring or rotating dish.
Pour into blender.
Blend until peas are broken up into small pieces.
tags: frozen green peas with cream sauce

title: fettuccine with turkey-mushroom sauce
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat.
Add fettuccine and cook according to package directions, stirring frequently until firm to the bite.
Drain in a colander.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Form sausage into 1 1/2-inch balls and fry.
Drain well. Marinate in sauce overnight made from the remaining ingredients. Heat in chafing dish and serve hot.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: egg pie
directions: In a blender, put all ingredients and whip.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 35 minutes or in a convection oven at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and rice.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add soup and rice mixture.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour water over all.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Cook until glaze effect and hard when dropped in water from spoon.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots 1/4-inch. Cook until fork-tender. Cook and mix with other ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: dump stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put all things together in large stew pot.
Cook until warmed through.
Simmer until ready to serve. Just mix up a pan of Jiffy cornbread and open a container of cottage cheese and you have a hot and hearty supper.
My men love this and it's so easy!

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for 10 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugar, add vanilla and water.
Mix in flour and beat until blended.
Stir in nuts, shape into small balls.
Bake 20 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Cool slightly on wire rack, roll in powdered sugar.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish. In a large mixing bowl, combine cheese, soups, chopped onion, butter, salt, and pepper. Mix well. Stir in hash browns. Place mixture
into a casserole dish, and stir together crushed cornflakes and 1 tbsp. butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill.

title: buckeye's
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter at medium speed with electric mixer until blended. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating after each addition until blended. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper and chill 10 to 15 minutes or until firm.

Microwave chocolate morsels and shortening in 2-quart glass bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until melted, stirring twice. Dip each ball into chocolate mixture until partially coated; place on wax paper to harden. Store in airtight container. Refrigerate overnight.	Mmmmmm.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a large pan. Add milk and mix well. Bring to a boil and cook until forms a soft ball in cold water. Stir constantly and remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and nuts. Beat until stiff. Pour in greased dish and cut when cool. (You can use peanut butter if you like.)

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Press each cookie down with a glass dipped into granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender. Drain. Mash and mix in margarine, soup, and bread crumbs. Add 1 1/4 c. cheese. Beat eggs and milk together. Stir in. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad with cream cheese
directions: In medium size bowl, mix all the ingredients together with the macaroni and chopped eggs.
A small amount of olive juice may be mixed with the cream cheese for flavor.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach, pressing against sides of sieve until all moisture is removed.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate (covered) for 24 hours.
Serve with corn chips, Melba rounds or tortilla chips.
Or with fresh vegetables.
Will keep 4 or 5 days and is delicious.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet.
Place in casserole dish. Mix juice, pineapple, sugar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread over chops. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crusty corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix with corn meal.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stir just until moistened.
Pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in hot oven 450° for 25-30 minutes.
If you prefer less flour in your corn bread, all or any part of the flour can be replaced with corn meal, making the recipe to your special taste.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, combine the apples and 2 tablespoons flour, tossing to coat the apples. Spoon into the pie shell.

title: quick delicious biscuits
directions: Mix
biscuit
mix,
sour
cream
and
Sprite
together; kneading only a few times.	Roll
out
dough to desired thickness and cut biscuits.
Dip
biscuits in the melted butter and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.	Cook at 350° until golden brown. These are very light and fluffy.

title: pink salmon croquettes
directions: Boil potato, peel and mash.
Remove bone from salmon.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Brown in hot oil until lightly browned on both sides.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples.
Pack tightly in crock-pot to top, filling it so lid will barely fit on.
Add apple cider. Cover and cook on low for 11 to 12 hours, stirring occasionally. Mash with large wooden spoon if still lumpy.
Add sugar and spices and cook an additional hour or until it is as thick as you like it.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: kielbasa
directions: Cut up kielbasa in small pieces.
Brown in frying pan.
Drain and cook kielbasa and all other ingredients in a crock-pot for at least 5 hours on low.

title: chicken-pepper sauce
directions: Heat gravy mix, water, sour cream and green pepper to boiling, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken spaghetti sauce(salsa di pollo)
directions: My mom's special light chicken sauce.

title: no cholesterol honey-apple cake
directions: Peel and thinly slice apples.
Put into large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
In another bowl, combine egg substitute, baking powder and oil.
Add water, honey and vanilla.
Combine.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan with vegetable oil.
Spread one-half of the dough into the pan.
Carefully layer apples over the top.
Pour in any juice from the apples.
Cover with the rest of the dough.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until top is golden brown.

title: tomato parmesan dressing
directions: Blend all in blender.
Makes 3/4 cup, or 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: barbara's soft raisin cookies
directions: Get Ready:
Heat oven to 325° (slow moderate).
Sift an ample amount of Gold Medal flour on a square of paper.

title: fruit pie
directions: Bake pie crusts.
Let cool.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and juice from pineapple and cherries.
If the juices do not make 1 cup, add water to finish.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick. Add cherries, pineapple and vanilla and mix well.
Let cool.
Add pecans and bananas to the mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in 2 baked pie crusts.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: philly chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: mom's pumpkin ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolk; add pumpkin, milk, sugar and spices.
Beat egg white, adding 1 tablespoon sugar.
Whip cream; mix with egg white. Add pumpkin mixture; freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan, without stirring.

title: macaroni dried beef casserole
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Stir once about halfway through cooking time and leave uncovered for last 1/2 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Place boneless chicken in 1 layer on bottom.
Add mushrooms and then sprinkle with cheese.
Spread soup over entire casserole.
Sprinkle with stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cover with can of tomato soup.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 90 minutes.
Serve with mustard sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion (drain).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Bake at 350°. Melt margarine. Combine all other ingredients. When margarine is cool, add to mixture and stir until combined. Line cookie sheet with foil or parchment paper. Drop 1/2 teaspoon dough onto lined sheet. Cookies will spread, so only put 3 to 4 on a line. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. When brown around edges, take out of oven and cool. Peel foil off the cookies; don't use spatula. Be very gentle; cookies crumble easily.

title: old fashioned dumplings
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring with a fork until moistened.
Turn dough out on well floured surface.
Knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Can make drop or rolled dumplings.
Roll dough and cut 4 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop 1 piece at a time into boiling broth.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cut okra in 1/2-inch pieces to make 3 cups.
Place onions, okra, tomatoes, margarine and brown sugar in saucepan; add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until thick.

title: italian-style meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Add Fritos when ready to serve.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and Bisquick until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms; beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on lightly greased cookie sheet. Make a shallow well in center of each with back of spoon.
Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake until golden in a 350° oven, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern style glazed carrots
directions: In large saucepan, cook carrots in boiling water to cover until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In same saucepan (because we all dislike doing dishes), combine remaining ingredients except pecans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add carrots and pecans; toss to coat with glaze mixture. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stove top hot dish
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing according to directions on the package. Cook the vegetables and add onion.
Mix the soup and sour cream and add to the vegetables.
Place dressing and vegetables in casserole; layer them.
Add leftover chicken or turkey, if you have it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar in a large bowl.	Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put first 4 ingredients in a medium-sized bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Good like this, but you can add toppings.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugars, milk and Karo syrup until it forms a soft ball stage.
Remove and add the peanut butter.
Beat until stiff.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut while still partially soft.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and butter; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water.
Cook until clear, 8 minutes.
Add 6 tablespoons of lemon juice and lemon rind; cook 2 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and milk; add slowly to mixture.
Cook to boil.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: candy brittle cookies
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with at least a 1/2-inch side with plain graham crackers.
Mix in pot the brown sugar and butter.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for at least 5 minutes.
Add pecans.
Spread over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cut while warm.
A pizza cutter does a good job. Try to fine the edges of the crackers first.

title: no fuss donuts
directions: Place biscuits on cutting board and cut center out with a thimble.
Save the holes.
Heat oil in Fry Daddy or frypan and brown on both sides.
Place fried donuts on paper towels.
In small bowl, mix powdered sugar with enough hot water to form a soft glaze.
Stir in vanilla. As soon as donuts are done, dip in glaze and place on rack to dry. Fry holes also and glaze.

title: crudites(fresh vegetables)
directions: Arrange attractively on a serving platter.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley.
Serve with Aioli Sauce.

title: coconut pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, stirring in chips and pecans last. Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Wash potatoes off.
Cook potatoes until boiling in jackets (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Let cool, slice in half.
Put sliced potatoes in baking pan and add cheese and bacon bits.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion.
Cook and stir over medium heat, until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Continue to cook and stir for 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in spinach.
Remove from heat.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and ice cream together until ice cream is melted.
Add last 2 ingredients and pour in oiled mold and put in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, pineapple, cream cheese and sugar.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill overnight.
Cut in slices.
Serve with picante sauce if desired.

title: deviled biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place in two 8-inch baking pans. Combine deviled ham and butter in small saucepan.
Heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: steak and onion pie
directions: In a Dutch oven, lightly brown onion in shortening. Meanwhile, combine flour, salt, pepper, ginger and allspice in a plastic bag.
Place meat cubes in the bag, a few pieces at a time, and shake well to coat.
Remove onion and set aside.
Brown beef on all sides.
Add water; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes and carrots; cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in peas and continue cooking until all vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Roll pastry out to a 10-inch square; place over meat mixture and seal edges to pan. Cut several small steam vents in crust.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pastry is browned.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine and simmer 30 minutes.
Grated cheese may be added to each serving.
Eat with chips.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla; stir in chopped pecans.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 250°.
Continue baking 30 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan. Chill.
Brush with syrup; top with pecan halves.

title: beef stew
directions: Salt, pepper and garlic powder stew meat.
Roll in flour to cover meat.
Brown meat in oil on all sides and remove from large skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery and saute until tender.
Add soup and water and return meat to skillet, blending all together.
Add carrots, potatoes, peas and Worcestershire sauce and cook over low heat about 2 hours.
Add more water as needed.

title: chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Pat into bottom of 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch glass baking dish.

title: cranberry orange molds
directions: Put cranberries and orange rind through food chopper.
Dice oranges.
Add oranges and sugar to cranberry mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool.
Add gelatin to cranberry mix. Pour into oiled molds.
Chill until firm.

title: oven fried herb chicken
directions: Add 12 skinned chicken drumsticks or 3 lbs. skinned chicken parts to mixture in dish. Turn to coat all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Let chill 30 min.
Preheat oven to 375°.
One piece at a time, remove from yogurt mixture and coat with crush Bran Flakes.
Arrange in a single layer in pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until tender.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 2/3 cup of liquid; mix well.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture on floured surface. Roll 1/2 of the dough to line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet (up sides).
Sprinkle dough with corn flakes; top with apples. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Roll remaining dough to make top crust and place over apples.
Seal edges of dough all around.
Cut slits in top.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar glaze while warm.
Cut into bars when cool.
A great breakfast treat.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Pour into muffin tin or make in pan.
If batter is too thick, add a little water.

title: okra stew
directions: Cook beef in large skillet; drain grease from meat.
Add half of diced onion.
Cook on medium low for about 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and pour reserved liquid in cans to get all sauce. Stir thoroughly.
Add green pepper and remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 20 minutes while preparing okra.
Put butter, remaining onion and okra in large Dutch kettle and cook on medium low for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add chopped tomatoes; continue cooking about 10 minutes.
Pour meat sauce over okra mixture; cover and let simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice or by itself as soup with crackers or cornbread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, soup, cheese, sour cream, onions and 3/4 cup butter, melted.
Put mixture in greased casserole dish. Crush chips and mix with remaining melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop Oreo cookies in blender until it looks like dirt.
Put into a large bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip until slightly thickened. Combine the butter mixture with the pudding mixture and blend.

title: lemon meringue pie(9-inch)
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and water. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Slowly stir half of the hot mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks. Then beat into hot mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup, beaten eggs and cheese in a large bowl. Gently fold in cooled broccoli.
Place in a greased round casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 300° oven until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half; place 1 half on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets, jelly roll style.
Tie securely with string.
On wax paper combine flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cutlets and toss gently to coat.
In large nonstick skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add cutlets. Cook, turning frequently, until golden (about 3 minutes). Add broth, wine and dried oregano to skillet.
Increase heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until chicken is cooked through and sauce is slightly thickened (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Place on serving plate and remove string. Garnish with parsley and oregano sprigs.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and garlic.
Add Prego.
Cook lasagne noodles 10 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
I use 3 noodles on bottom 2 layers.
Then on top layer 2 noodles, remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese only.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon in small bowl with pastry blender.
Blend margarine into mixture.
Add nuts.
Spoon over batter.

title: kittie's cinnamon rolls
directions: Brush on top while still hot.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in evaporated milk.
Then coat thoroughly with crushed corn flakes.
Place pats of butter or margarine over chicken.
Pour remaining evaporated milk over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 60-90 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Empty oyster crackers in a large container. Pour oil and sprinkle with dressing over crackers and stir every time you open the refrigerator. Place in refrigerator for 24 hours in a tight container.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain.
Spoon beans into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Top with beef, chilies, salsa and cheese in layers. Top with sour cream, olives and green onions.
Serve with chips.

title: hawaiian rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw frozen dough according to directions.
Spread 3 tablespoons of butter on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons brown sugar, 1/2 coconut and crushed pineapple.
Roll dough out to 13 x 15-inches.
Brush with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up tightly, starting with the long end.
Cut into 15 pieces and place cut up side in prepared pan.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Turn out on waxed paper and cool on wire rack.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Melt jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until thickened, but not firmly jelled.
Then add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill in a shallow dish until set.

title: pickled okra
directions: Stuff okra in jars.
Add hot pepper or dill.
Bring all other ingredients to boil.
Pour liquid over okra in jars and seal.
Let stand for 2 weeks.

title: corn soup
directions: Fry bacon; remove pieces and drain on paper towel.
Add onion and potatoes to drippings; cover and simmer until done.
Change to larger pot.
Start with milk and warm, then add corn and also onion and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper and butter.

title: church casserole
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on package. Mix all ingredients together. Spread shredded cheese on top. Microwave 10 minutes or put in oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and whole egg until very light. Beat in milk and salt. Stir in and work with hands the flour. Divide dough into 3 parts. Roll out each piece as thin as possible (paper thin) on a lightly floured board. Place dough on floured surface until partially dry. Roll dough as for jelly roll. With a thin sharp knife, cut into strips of desired width (1/8-inch) for fine noodles, up to 1/2-inch for broad noodles. Shake out the strips and allow to dry before using or storing.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Add all except 1 can of soup. Pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole (or 2 smaller ones). Pour other can soup over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Freezes well. Thaw before cooking.

title: san francisco chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and salt with a fork.
Melt butter and add garlic.
Simmer gently for 3 minutes.
Dip each breast into the butter mixture and then into bread mixture.
Roll each up tightly and fasten with toothpick.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and the remaining butter and a dash of paprika on each piece.
Bake 1 hour, basting twice.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Don't grease the pan.
Beat the egg yolks until lemon color. Add the sugar gradually.
Add the orange juice and the rind.
Add the flour with the salt.
Sift together once.
Beat the egg whites and fold into the mixture.

title: a seven devils sandwich mt. belizel
directions: Open bun on cookie sheet.
Place roast beef on open bun.
Put drained sauerkraut on next.
Top with 4 slices American cheese and cook at 350° until good and hot with cheese melted and bun toasted. Layer with mayonnaise and lettuce.
Serve halved with chips and pickles.
Delicious.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa (dry), removing all lumps.
Add margarine, milk and syrup.
Cook on medium heat until forms soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
Set pot in cool water, stirring until thick.
Pour in buttered dish.
When it hardens, cut in squares and remove from dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and softened butter.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add alternately with the milk to the sugar mixture.
Add flavorings. Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter together.
Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla, sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Add flour mixing by hand until blended well.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: electric skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Set skillet at 340°.
Add sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Stir until mixture comes to boil; stir constantly.
Count time from boil 5 minutes.
Turn skillet off.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Put into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool; cut into 36 pieces.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal with meat mallet; coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper, shaking off excess.
Brown in 1/4 cup butter in large skillet over medium heat for 2 minutes on each side.
Remove to warm platter.
Add lemon juice and wine to skillet, stirring with wooden spoon to deglaze.
Add capers.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, stirring just until butter is well mixed; remove from heat.
Pour over veal.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: best waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour onto hot waffle iron or onto griddle for pancakes.

title: milk chocolate florentine cookies
directions: Cookie:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, sugar, flour, corn syrup, milk, vanilla extract and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls about 3-inches apart onto foil-lined cookie sheets. Spread thin with rubber spatula.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely.
Peel foil away from cookies.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix all together.
Divide 2 cans crescent rolls into 16 parts. Spoon chicken mixture in center of each roll.
Fold the roll over until all of the chicken is covered.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts until meat can fall off bones.
Let cool. In a separate large pan, put in cans of chicken broth and bouillon cube.
Season with celery, salt and pepper.
Also carrots and celery.
Boil until vegetables are tender.
Now add noodles. Cook until noodles are done.
If too thin, use cornstarch to thicken by using directions on box of cornstarch.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool and cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well after each. Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Mix well. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture; beat well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whites. Pour into 3 deep 5 or 9-inch layer pans lined on bottom with paper. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix well ahead of time.
Take portion of punch and freeze a ring mold.
When ready to serve, let mold float on punch; also may float orange ring on top.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons or 50 servings.

title: festive holiday salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine jello and sugar.
Add water; stir until jello and sugar are dissolved.
Stir in pineapple, cranberries, apples, celery and walnuts.
Chill until firm in jello mold 3 to 4 hours.

title: layered green salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer ingredients in order as follows: lettuce, cauliflower, onion, bacon and cheese.
Ice the salad with mayonnaise, sealing the edges carefully.
Sprinkle sugar over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: danny's french toast
directions: Prepare sausage as label directs; drain.
Cut eight (1 1/2-inch thick) slices from bread.
Cut a pocket into each.
Fit cheese and sausage into pockets.
Press together.
In bowl, beat with a fork the eggs, milk and sugar.
Add stuffed bread and turn.
Heat small amount of salad oil in skillet over medium heat.
Cook sandwiches about 10 minutes, until golden.

title: raspberry swirl cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth, add eggs and 3 Tbsp. lemon juice; mix well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Dip and bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Don't overcook.
Overcooking will make cookies dry and crumbly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine beverage and catsup, stirring until well blended. Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: zucchini apple bread
directions: Separate the breadsticks into 8 pieces, leaving them coiled. Place the coils 3 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet. Press each coil into a 4-inch circle.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly before slicing.
Arrange cucumbers and onions in layers in earthenware crock or bowl.
Sprinkle each layer with salt.
Cover; let stand 3 hours.
Drain off juice which has accumulated.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed; bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Boil for 3 minutes.
Add cucumber mixture; bring once more to boiling point, but do not boil.
Pack immediately into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Layer ham and cheese between top and bottom layer of rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until margarine melts and blends with the rest.
Cover rolls with mixture.
Leave uncovered until mixture thickens (10 minutes). Cover with foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese 10 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 5 minutes more.
Add flour and then pecans.
Add eggs, alternately as mixing.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes a beautiful Bundt cake.

title: flawless fudge
directions: Heat chocolate and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; blend in vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread in buttered 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm; cut in small squares.
Makes about 18 pieces.

title: vegetable chili
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, chop green peppers and onion. Cut zucchini and yellow squash lengthwise into quarters. Cut each quarter crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: sweet potato chips(fat free)
directions: Peel and slice paper thin.
Place in cold ice water for 2 hours to "crisp."
Serve with favorite dip.

title: barbara's banana bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly with an electric mixer.
Pour the batter into two 4 x 8-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it tests done.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: hoska
directions: In small saucepan, scald milk.
Stir in shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Stir yeast in warm water until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, then 2 eggs, then 3 cups flour.
With spoon, beat until smooth.
Stir in raisins, citron, chopped almonds and about 2 1/2 cups of flour (or enough to make stiff dough).
On lightly floured surface, knead dough until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease all sides.
Cover with towel. Let rise in warm place (85°) about 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down dough. Turn on floured surface.
Divide in half, then divide halves into 3 equal pieces.
Roll each piece between hands into strips 18 inches long.
Place on greased cookie sheet and braid.
Brush top with butter.
Put next braid on top.
Let rise 1 hour until doubled in bulk.
Beat 1 egg and water and brush over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, olives, walnuts, onions and cheese.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Make a mixture of 1/2 Marzetti's Dressing and 1/2 Miracle Whip, enough to achieve desired consistency.
Stir mixture into other ingredients.
Chill. Serves 4.

title: black forest torte
directions: Prepare cake as directed in 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Cool. Slice both cakes in half. Place 1 cake slice and cover with some cherry pie filling.
Place top layer of cake and more filling. Repeat with last two sections of cake.
Ice cake with Cool Whip. Place dab of pie filling in center.
Decorate with chocolate curls.

title: french omelet
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; beat in milk and seasonings.
Pour into hot oil in a skillet over low heat.
Cook slowly.
As under surface becomes set, lift edges slightly with spatula to let uncooked portion flow underneath and cook.
To add herbs, cheese or meat, sprinkle 1/2 tablespoon per egg while cooking.
As soon as all mixture is set, fold over and serve immediately.
When adding green peppers, onion or bacon, cook before adding to omelet.
Serves 2.

title: foil baked chicken
directions: Place rice, hot water, onion soup and mushroom soup in 9 x 13-inch pan; mix well.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rachel's noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles.
Do not rinse noodles; strain thoroughly.
Mix sour cream and softened cream cheese.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, vanilla, sugar, raisins and cinnamon.

title: chicken, hungarian style
directions: Cut chicken in quarters and flour lightly.
Cook to a light brown with onion (chopped fine) and the garlic.
Add the sour cream and salt.
Cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Lay chicken on rice.
Cover with sauce and serve.

title: peanut pudding cake
directions: Layer 1:
In a small bowl, thoroughly mix 2/3 cup peanuts, flour and butter.
Press into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix together.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to wet ingredients with wire whisk.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add onions, celery and parsley; saute until tender.
Run slices of bread under cold water until moist (not soaking) and mash with hands.
When mixed well, add onions, celery, parsley and spices; mix well with a large spoon. Put in roasting pan around chicken or turkey about 1 1/2 hours before meat is done.
Baste with juices of meat occasionally for flavor and moistness.
Seasoning may be adjusted to suit your taste.

title: french crullers
directions: Combine sugar, salt, Crisco and water in saucepan; heat to a brisk boil.
Add flour all at once, stirring vigorously with a wooden spoon.
Beat until mixture forms a smooth ball that will leave the sides of the pan.
Place in a bowl.
Beat in eggs one at a time, then continue beating until mixture is smooth and shiny. Add vanilla.
Chill mixture.
Now force mixture through a pastry tube.
Make into rings on oiled wax paper.
Drop into hot oil at 380° and brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Mix in basil and celery seed.
Add kielbasa.
Melt brown sugar into warm water.
Drizzle over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°, or put in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Cook meat, seasoning, onions, celery and green peppers until meat has browned some.
Drain fat.
Add rice, tomato juice, corn and green beans.
Add Velveeta over top.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: deviled cheese filled franks
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; mix cheese with fork until it has a smooth, buttery consistency.
Add pickle relish, mustard, chili sauce and salad dressing; mix well.
Split franks almost through lengthwise.
Fill franks with deviled cheese mixture. Grill or broil until franks are hot and cheese is slightly melted.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the crackers and pour into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered for about 45 minutes.

title: fat free icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and it's ready to go on the cake!

title: basic roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Cool milk to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast, egg and 2 cups of flour.
Beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour or enough to make dough soft.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface. Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut rounds of dough with a 1 3/4-inch cutter. Shape in small balls.
Brush each with butter.
Cover and let double (25 to 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Fry ham and pork until no pink is showing.
Put in large kettle, then fry each vegetable separately, except carrots (parboil them), then drain and add to meat.
Season to taste.
You can fry green pepper and celery together.
(Cut celery on bias.) Put everything in big pot with meat.
Cook slow for 1 1/2 hours.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Set aside.
Place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) in following order:
bread slices on bottom.
Add sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
This dish can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Use extra water if necessary to make mixture real soft so it will pour.
Pour into a greased baking pan about 3-inches deep and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until well set and brown on top.
Suitable for freezing for a short time.

title: peanut chocolate balls
directions: Melt chips and paraffin over hot water (use double boiler). Dip peanut balls into coating mix while hot.
Place on wax paper.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix corned beef, celery, eggs and onions.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add to above mixture.
Stir well and pour in mold.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer, about 2 minutes, or until smooth and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and soda, gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 13-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Yields one (10-inch) cake.

title: pancakes
directions: With wire whisk or hand beater, beat until well blended.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle (greased if necessary); cook until edges are dry.
Turn over until golden.
Makes 12 or 13 pancakes.
For thinner pancakes, use 1 1/2 cups of milk.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Saute garlic one minute while stirring.
Add pine nuts and stir for two minutes.
Add broccoli which has been cut into approximately 1-inch pieces.
Saute and stir until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Add cooked, well drained pasta and toss several times.
Serve with grated cheese on top and pepper to taste.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown and cook ground beef in skillet, strain meat if necessary.
Mix can of soup and green beans.
Peel and cook potatoes, mash with butter and milk.
Put ground beef in bottom of baking dish then layer soup mixture on top.
Then layer mashed potatoes on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: oriental fruit salad
directions: Mix rice, marshmallows, Cool Whip, then sweeten with the sugars; add fruit.
Keeps well.
Better if you mix and let set for awhile or overnight.

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Measure corn flakes cereal.
Crush to 1 cup.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix only until combined.
Shape into 6 loaves, about 4 inches long.
Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each loaf with one-half slice cheese.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Cream until smooth. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, with milk and flour.
Mix well after each addition.
End with flour and vanilla flavoring.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread and cool.
Crumble in a 2-quart dish.
Slice and dice rest of recipe. Mix together and refrigerate.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese, in order given.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour into greased dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake until rice is tender, then top with cheese and brown.

title: date dainties
directions: Variation:
Add 1/2 cup coconut or nut meats with cereal.

title: corn rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Combine onion, pepper, corn, egg, sugar, pimento and water.
Stir in rice.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let stand until cheese melts.

title: southern fried hominy
directions: Fry bacon; add onion.
Stir-fry in the hominy for five minutes, until hot.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, 7-Up, cornstarch and jello over low heat until very thick.
Change color-clear.
Add 1 package strawberry jello and dissolve in 1/2 cup hot water.
Let cool.
Put strawberries in pie shell, pour filling over strawberries, then top with Cool Whip.

title: prune whip
directions: Combine
prunes,
sugar, vanilla
and egg whites.
Beat until mixture is light in color, increased in volume and quite dry. Chill thoroughly.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Mash hot potatoes in large bowl. When all lumps are removed, add cream cheese in small pieces; add butter.
Beat well until completely mixed.
Mix in sour cream. Add eggs and onion to milk, then add to potato mixture along with salt and pepper.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese, milk and salt; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add additional salad dressing just before serving, if desired.
Serve on lettuce-covered platter.
Serves 4.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Add peanut butter and powdered sugar to very soft butter.
Mix very well.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Put or pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate or butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Spread on top of bars.
Let harden and cut into small bars.
No bake, but I keep it in refrigerator.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and butter.
Mash into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: brownies with frosting
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a jelly roll pan (10 X 15).
Frost while still warm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool.

title: easy-shrimp scampi
directions: In large skillet, add all ingredients, then add shrimp.
Cook until pink.
Pour over rice (cooked).
Serve warm.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry Jell-O.
Add 2 cups hot water and mix well.
Then add 2 cups cold water.
Let chill.
Add nuts and pineapple.

title: lasagna(makes 2 pans)
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles, while simmering meat sauce, in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine Cool Whip and yogurt.
Add mashed strawberries and mix well.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.
Makes 5 cups.
Recipe can be halved.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts; salt to taste.
Debone chicken and cut into chunks.
Keep broth.
Line large casserole with tortillas dipped in chicken broth.
In layers, put chicken, onion, bell pepper, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Take tomatoes and drain off some of juice.
Add 2 tablespoons jalapeno relish and mash together.
Add layer of tomato relish and add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in a large, shallow dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 12.

title: brandied cheese ball
directions: Beat butter with cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add salt and parsley.
Gradually beat in Monterey Jack cheese.
Beat in brandy a little at a time.
Chill cheese mixture.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies mix in a jar
directions: Mix until completely blended.
You will need to finish mixing with your hands.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Place 2-inches apart on a parchment-lined or lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes, until edges are lightly browned. Cool 5 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove cookies to baking racks to finish cooling.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate nut fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Let come to boil.
Turn heat on medium and let boil until you drop a drop of mixture into a cup of cold water and it forms a hard ball.
Remove from stove.
Add margarine, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixture starts to thicken.

title: pineapple-filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs, fruit juices, flour and salt.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.

Stir in chicken, 1 can cream of chicken soup, sour cream, mushrooms, green chilies, almonds, oregano, salt and pepper, mixing well. Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate bit squares
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, margarine, vanilla and a few drops of water.
Add 2 eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
If too stiff, add a few more drops of water.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread into a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with edge.
Sprinkle bag of chocolate chips over the batter and put into a 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and run a knife over pan both ways to marbelize, then return to oven for 12 minutes.

title: country casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Line bottom of casserole with bread and sausage.
Mix eggs, cheese, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight (very important).
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in scalded milk.
Add oleo to melt in hot milk and, when nearly cool, add egg.
Dissolve yeast in warm water with a teaspoon of the sugar.
Add this to milk mixture. Put in half of the flour at one time and mix well.
Stir in the rest of the flour.
Put dough into a greased bowl.
Cover lightly with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down dough and add flour as needed to handle.
Knead dough until it blisters.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover lightly with plastic and let rise to double. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: smoked beef and cream cheese dip
directions: Take a sharp knife and cut through the smoked chipped beef loaf until it is in tiny pieces.
Place it in a bowl with the cream cheese and mix together.
Add enough horseradish to suit your own taste.
When everything is mixed together, store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: katie's christmas trees
directions: Cream together Crisco, peanut butter, white and brown sugars. Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix together well.
Take 1 teaspoon cookie dough and roll in ball.
Then roll ball in white sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place on one Hershey's chocolate Kiss on each cookie and press in until cookie cracks.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Cool on rack.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pans (use 1 large ring pan or three 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch loaf pans) and bake about 1 hour at 350°, until cake tests done and starts to leave sides of pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Very good plain or with softened cream cheese.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Work together persimmons, buttermilk and soda.
Run through colander and add butter mixed with sugar, eggs and potato.
Add flour and spices and mix.
Bake in thin layers at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stack while hot and serve with cream.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. Gradually add sugar; beat until peaks form.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven; turn oven off.
Leave in overnight until the next morning.

title: all american cake
directions: Cut cake in half (bottom and top layers).
Spread one cup of yogurt over bottom half of cake.
Top with half of berries.
Place top layer of cake over berries and yogurt.
Spread the other cup of yogurt and berries over the top.
Makes 10 servings, 197 calories/fat.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Very lightly spray cookie sheet.
In a small bowl mix together all ingredients except potatoes.

Put cut potatoes in medium bowl. Mix in oil mixture until all potatoes are coated. Arrange on baking sheet, cut side down. Bake 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender inside and undersides are crusty brown.

title: instant pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Turn stove burner on medium-high heat.
Lightly grease skillet or griddle and when it's hot, pour batter on in pancake form and let brown. Turn only once.
Serve hot with syrup.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: i can't believe its peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll into balls- press with fork on slightly greased pan.

title: deviled eggs(no fat, no cholesterol; very good)
directions: Note:
If you prefer a sweet taste, use less mustard and add 1 to 2 tablespoons sweet pickle relish.

title: chicken n mac
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add other ingredients; stir.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in approximately 2-inch layers in crock-pot: ham, potatoes, onions and cheese.
Pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) on top of layers.
Cook on low heat until done.

title: swiss steak supreme
directions: Flour cube steaks; place in greased and floured shallow baking pan in single layer.
Sprinkle dry Lipton onion soup mix over the steaks.
Mix mushroom or celery soup with 3/4 can of water or milk; pour over the steaks.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Foil may be removed during the last 15 minutes to brown steaks.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening until mixture is coarse and grainy.	Using
pastry
blender,
mix buttermilk into mixture.
Do not overmix.
Put on flour board and knead a few times.
Cut with
floured	cutter.
Place	1
tablespoon Crisco in heavy pan and put in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove the pan and place the cut biscuits in it, turning each once in the oil.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy ravioli
directions: Blot dry peppers; cut into thin strips.
Cook ravioli according to package directions; drain and combine with pepper strips and dressing in a large nonstick skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is hot.
Garnish with cheese.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender.
Drain and cool. Separate onion and add with green pepper. In blender, combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend well. Pour over carrots and toss lightly.
Marinate overnight.
Serves 10.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread 3 hours and break into small pieces.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Add the seasoning and the vegetables. Spread 2/3 cornbread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar or Colby cheese.
Top with meat and vegetable mixture.
Top with remaining cornbread.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check by inserting a toothpick.

title: ginger-and-peach chicken
