directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Over medium heat cook chicken in prepared skillet 8 to 10 minutes until browned and no longer pink.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
In 1-cup measuring cup place reserved peach syrup; add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Stir in cornstarch, ginger root and salt.
In same skillet cook peach syrup mixture, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add reserved chicken, water chestnuts and pea pods. Cook until heated through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Remove the crusts and butter the bread. Grease a baking dish and line the base and sides with slices of the bread. Sprinkle with the orange juice and rind. Add half the sultanas, another layer of bread, the rest of the sultanas and then more bread (if you have any left).
Beat eggs well in a bowl. Add milk and sugar and pour into the baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until set and browning nicely.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and margarine over low heat. Stir in
remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and discard liquid from all beans.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil the sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil.
Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep several days.

title: super bowl chili
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown the beef and pork.
Drain off excess fat.
Add undrained chili or kidney beans and tomatoes, chopped onions, garlic, chili powder, sugar, red pepper and vinegar.
Cover and simmer chili for 1 hour, stirring frequently to avoid scorching.
Serve in bowls topped with shredded Cheddar cheese and sour cream (optional).
Makes 6 to 8 main dishes.

title: baked fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together; gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla.
Sift flour with salt; add to chocolate mixture, along with the nuts.
Spread in buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool and cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen.
Makes 36.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Allow cream cheese, butter and eggs to reach room temperature. Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in flour, gently by hand.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Bring to a boil and add 1 cup self-rising flour.
Roll out to fit pie plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer shredded lettuce, thinly sliced red onion and mayonnaise mixture (mayonnaise, sugar and salt); sprinkle bacon bits, broccoli and cheeses.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: death-by-chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Divide batter into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Cook according to package directions.
Use one cake only.
Freeze the other cake for later use.
Using the handle of a wooden spoon, poke holes throughout the cake.
Cover holes well with Hershey's syrup.
Crush Oreo cookies and sprinkle over cake. Mix pudding with milk and pour on top.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, cover with Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate chips, crushed Oreos or syrup.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and dip in melted butter. Mix rice with soup and spread in large shallow buttered casserole dish. Top with chicken breasts and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry-pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, honey and butter; press into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper while boiling.
Place deboned chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Top with combined broth, chicken soup and vegetables.
Combine flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: tangy french dressing
directions: Shake well in jar or mix in blender.
Store in refrigerator. Yield:
approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: "easy as pie" cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed (adding flour), using only the whites of the required eggs.
Substitute the amount of required oil with an equal amount of applesauce.
Follow directions for mixing on cake mix package and pour into lightly sprayed or buttered pan. Bake according to directions.
Cool before removing from pan. Frost, if desired.

title: carol's meal in the pan
directions: In frypan, fry potatoes and onions in butter until 3/4 done or heated through and turning brown.
Sprinkle meat, mushrooms and pepper on top.
Steam a few minutes until heated through.
Pour eggs over all and when almost cooked, sprinkle cheese on top. When melted, it's done.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Stir in dry ingredients (that have been sifted together); add flavoring.

title: microwave sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Combine mustard and jelly in 1-cup glass measure.
Cover with plastic wrap; cook on 60% power for 3 minutes.
Cut each frankfurter diagonally into 8 slices.
Place butter and franks in 1-quart glass casserole; cover.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve hot on toothpicks.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add butter, canned milk, and 2% milk.
Add eggs, cheese (save some for the top), and salt and pepper.
Mix together well and put in crock pot.
Cook on low for approx. 3 hours.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake(low-fat)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk and pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Place drained peaches on batter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: bran muffin treats
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Combine cereal and milk in another bowl.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in egg whites and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon batter into cupcake papers or greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cindy's best shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl.
Sprinkle with quite a bit of cumin and garlic powder.
Sprinkle lightly with red pepper.
Use tomatoes and green chilies out of Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Fold in drained shrimp.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add the next 4 ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes. Add 1/3 of the shredded cheese. Season to taste. (We like it hot!)
Line a baking dish with corn chips.
Pour soup over chips and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Bake until hot at 350°.

title: b c pie
directions: Take pie crust; chill for 20 minutes.
While pie crust is chilling, place cream cheese in a large bowl.
Let stand to soften.
When cream cheese is soft, mix with mixer.
Add sugar to taste until good consistency is desired.
Spread some of the cream cheese on pie crust, then place 1/2 of the blueberry filling in the crust, then add the rest of the cream cheese over filling very carefully.
Put the rest of the blueberries on top.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, butter, vanilla and powdered sugar. Roll into balls. Melt the shortening and chocolate chips. Dip the balls into chocolate and leave on wax paper to set.

title: chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl at the same time.
Mix with spoon (do not use electric mixer).
Put in an 8-inch pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana layer dessert
directions: Soak bananas in pineapple juice for 10 minutes.
Mix crushed crackers with 1 stick melted oleo.
Beat eggs, sugar and 2 sticks melted oleo together for 15 minutes.
Arrange in layers:
graham cracker crumbs, sugar mixture, bananas, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill 8 hours.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Spread over filling; bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool and chill well.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except corn flake crumbs and butter. Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with corn flake crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add rest of ingredients; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with a potato masher (I don't).
Add milk and cheese. Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Yields 10 cups.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Combine punch and lemonade.
Freeze in ice trays.
Add ginger ale over ice cubes just before serving.

title: incredible double chocolate cheesecake
directions: Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Heat oven to 300°.
Stir together butter and cocoa until smooth; set aside.
In large bowl, beat cheese.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes. Remove from oven to wire rack; loosen cake from rim.
Refrigerate. Garnish with whipped cream and a little cocoa around top edge. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix lime juice, salad dressing and butter and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with plain or seasoned rice.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes on low heat.
Then add vanilla.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Make mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.
Will keep a long time.

title: butternut squash bake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in squash (mixture will be thin).
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until almost set.

title: carrot latkes
directions: Put eggs in a bowl, and beat with a fork.
Wash and peel carrots, and grate into bowl.
Add rest of ingredients, and mix well.

title: garden rice salad
directions: Saute garlic, onion, carrot, celery, parsley, basil
and oregano in a small amount of water until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes, beans and rice.

title: plantation pralines
directions: Combine sugars, cream of tartar, salt and milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 235° to 238°, approximately 12 minutes.
Add butter, extract and pecans.
Beat until creamy. Drop from large spoon onto buttered surface or waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen pralines.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hungarian lentil soup(low-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients, except cooked meat or poultry, in a soup pot or pressure cooker.
Cover and cook 50 to 60 minutes (or 15 to 20 minutes, under pressure, according to manufacturer's directions).
Season to taste and stir in diced meat, if desired; heat through.
Makes 4 meal-size servings.

title: weepless meringue
directions: Mix together cornstarch and cold water in small saucepan.
Stir in boiling water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for about 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool. Add cream of tartar to egg whites, beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Add cornstarch mixture all at once.
Beat until well blended and very stiff.
Spread over pie filling and bake 15 to 18 minutes in 350° oven until lightly brown.

title: simple chicken
directions: In crock-pot, mix soup mix, basil, garlic and tomatoes.
Add vegetables, coat good with sauce.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Put on top of vegetables.
Cook until chicken is tender.

title: chili
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper together.
Drain excess grease.
Combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: fluffy coconut cake with pineapple filling
directions: Make sure the cornstarch is blended well in the warm water. Mix all ingredients together in a small saucepan.
Cook until it thickens.
Cool mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to spread.
(I usually prefer to make the filling before making the cake, then it is ready once the cake cools.)
Spread this filling between cake layers only.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order, except last cup of sugar.
Stir in last cup of sugar by hand.
Roll into balls and dip top in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Just bake until the bottoms start to turn brown, then remove the cookie sheet from the oven and leave the cookies on the cookie sheet for a little while.)

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, oil and salt and pepper. Pour over drained vegetables. Toss well; chill overnight. Toss again just before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water and orange juice real good.
Mix	all
ingredients together.
Pour into a mold and let set in refrigerator until molded.

title: pecan topped toffee
directions: In deep narrow saucepan, melt butter and sugar; boil to 300°, hard candy stage.
Stir constantly.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chocolate over hot candy; spread evenly when melted.
Sprinkle with pecans; press lightly.
Refrigerate 1 hour (no longer).
Turn out and break into pieces.

title: lemon-parsleyed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes tender.
Place in a serving bowl; keep warm. Meanwhile, melt butter; stir in parsley and lemon juice.
Pour over potatoes; stir lightly to coat.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Spread pecans in a shallow pan, and roast in a slow oven (325°) for about 10 minutes.
Pecans should be crisp, but not really browned.
Stir pecans twice during baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times.
Cream margarine and shortening well.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings and blend.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Beat well and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: strawberry punch *
directions: Blend the strawberries, ReaLemon and simple syrup in blender and chill.
To serve, add the ginger ale.
This makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix and chill several hours.
Can be frozen.

title: bologna cream cheese appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese, relish, pimento and onion.
Spread mixture thinly on each bologna slice; stack several slices.
Wrap with plastic wrap; chill or freeze.
Cut in small wedges with very sharp knife.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Heat butter and whiskey together.
Add other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to get semi-hard.
(Make balls about large marble size.)
If sticky, use powdered sugar on hands.

title: mocha torte
directions: Cut frozen pound cake horizontally in 5 or 7 layers.
Melt chocolate bits over low heat.
Remove from heat and add instant coffee and sour cream.
Frost each layer, stacking one on top of another to rebuild loaf.
Frost entire cake.
Chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 45 minutes, uncovered.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into sauce. Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until shrimp are done. Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: mom's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan. Over low heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly and then cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream and peanut butter, mixing well. Pour into a buttered pan and cool completely. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When done, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Add crushed candy bars and then caramel topping.
Gently spread over cake.

title: glazed wieners(microwave)
directions: Remove metal lid from marmalade jar.
Place jar in microwave oven.
Cook marmalade about 1 1/2 minutes or until heated throughout and marmalade melts.
Cut each wiener crosswise into 4 pieces.
Divide the round side of the wiener into fourths and cut into the edge 1/2 inch.
Place marmalade and wieners in an 8-inch ovenware cake dish.
Stir.
Cook in microwave oven 4 to 5 minutes or until wieners are hot.
Stir once during heating.
As the wieners heat, the cut ends spread apart and curl.
Add toothpicks and they are ready to serve.
Recipe yields 40 pieces.

title: gazebo cheese soup
directions: Saut onions and celery in butter. Add chicken broth, carrots and Tabasco and simmer 30 minutes. Add potato soup, cheese and sour cream. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a casserole dish, mix all of the ingredients, except the bread. Break the bread into pieces and drop into mixture to make thick consistency, but not too dry. Sprinkle some cinnamon on top and put some butter. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tangy pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in a skillet with a little oil. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook in small roaster at 325° for 2 hours or until done.
Baste at 1 hour, 1 1/2 hours and 1 3/4 hours.
Use sauce to pour over a side dish of rice.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add onion; cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour on low heat.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 2/3 cup sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until moisture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add a small amount to egg yolks.
Stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cool.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch nonstick pan with cover, then break up noodles into pan; lightly brown egg noodles.
Then stir in rice and broth.
Bring to a boil, then cover pan and lower heat until broth is almost all gone.
Remove pan.
Cover and stir up the rice until all the broth is gone, then service.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: girl scout punch
directions: Mix Hi-C and ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add sherbet. Cherries or crushed pineapple can be added for variation.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: *Or place 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar in 1/2 cup measure; fill with milk.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together in a large bowl by hand.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meaty manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
Brown ground beef in medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Remove from heat and add spinach, cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper (to taste).
Stir until well mixed.
Fill each shell with 1/4 cup meat mixture.
Place filled shells in prepared baking pan. Pour spaghetti sauce evenly over filled shells.
Sprinkle Parmesan, then Mozzarella, over all.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chuck roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for 6 to 7 hours.
Tear apart and pick the fat out.

title: rose-wine spritzer
directions: Pour
Rose
wine and club soda into large pitcher; stir just to combine.
Using a sharp knife, remove skin from lemon in
one spiral.
Spear
one
end of spiral with metal skewer. Wind	peel around skewer and spear other end.	Top with lemon wedge.
Stand in	pitcher.
Serve in wine glasses or tall ice filled glasses. Makes about 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, oil, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except zucchini.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli, chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute the green pepper and onions in the 4 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add diced chicken and saute until just done (do not overcook).
Add and stir until smooth, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Place slaw ingredients in layers in large bowl.
First, place in cabbage, next onion, green pepper and, last, carrots.
Pour over 1 cup sugar.
Do not stir!
Bring to boil the vinegar, salad oil, salt and sugar; pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Do not stir until ready to serve.
For best results, allow to sit overnight, covered and refrigerated.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chocolate and margarine with Eagle Brand, water and vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly until thick about 5 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, but omit butter.
Mix ingredients and toss.
If not moist enough, add liquid from drained artichokes, salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.
Better if made a few hours before serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients with bacon, broken into bits. Pour over croutons and cheese.
Arrange sausages on top to form pinwheel design.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
(Could use ham bits instead of bacon.)

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Cut fish into strips like French fries.
Marinate in Heinz 57 or A.1. sauce overnight.
Coat fish with pancake mix or Bisquick. Fry in hot oil.

title: caramel chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When removed from oven, take a spoon on its side and make several cuts (20) all the way through the cake.

Pour condensed milk over the entire cake into holes. Follow by putting the ice cream topping in the holes, as desired. Let cake cool completely, put in the refrigerator and, when cold, apply Cool Whip and crunched candy bars.

title: turkey-tortilla casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Heat oil over medium heat in a large nonstick skillet.
Cook onion and garlic until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add turkey, chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper, oregano and vinegar.
Cook until turkey is no longer pink.
Stir in black beans and remove from heat.
Combine salsa and chicken broth; spread a thin layer of salsa mix in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of tortilla strips, half of turkey mix and 1/2 of remaining salsa mix.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with cheese. Bake until bubbly hot, about 25 minutes, or microwave on 70% power for 15 minutes.
Top each serving with a spoon of yogurt.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: *Can fry or put under broiler.

title: easy bars
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate in top of double boiler. Heat until melted.
Spread marshmallows in buttered 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add peanuts. Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: peaches 'n cream pie(peach halves served sunny-side-up in a rich sauce)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, orange peel and cranberry sauce in saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Gently stir in apples; set aside.

title: cocoa puff ball
directions: Boil the sugar, Karo syrup and chocolate chips to full boil, about 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over Cocoa Puffs.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
(Put butter on your hands and make into ball after dropping on wax paper.)

title: sausage-macaroni casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet. Pour off drippings. Add flour and salt, blending well. Gradually add milk and cook over heat, stirring until thickened. Stir in macaroni and 1 cup of cheese. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Break chocolate squares in half (melt in microwave with oleo and vanilla).
When melted, add marshmallow cream.
Blend all together and set aside.
Combine sugar and canned milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
When a small amount in cold water forms a soft ball, pour over mixture and blend.
When blended, add peanut butter.
Put in refrigerator; leave overnight. Remove next day and cut; remove from pan.
Keep stored in refrigerator after cutting.
Take out when you are ready to serve the fudge.

title: zesty flank steak
directions: Slice steak very thin.
Rub dressing and peppercorns into steak and allow to marinate 30 minutes.
Place steak on broiler rack and broil for 8 minutes.
Turn steak, then pour marinade over steak.
Broil 8 more minutes.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Serve.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work flour, vanilla and nuts into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased pan for 30 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Roll hot tarts in powdered sugar.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheese balls
directions: Make into balls and serve with chips, crackers, etc.

title: apple salsa and cinnamon chips
directions: Peel, core and chop apples into a 1-quart bowl. Cut strawberries into small pieces and add to apples. Add kiwi. Cut orange and squeeze juice into bowl; then remove as much pulp as you can and add to juice.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat well. Garnish with grated Cheddar cheese, raw onion and green olives.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve 1 envelope Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in 1 cup very hot tomato soup (off stove, do not add water to soup) until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika after removing from mold onto serving plate.
Use various types of crackers: wheat, rye, etc. and enjoy.

title: crunchy carrot-pineapple mold(serves 16)
directions: Heat pineapple and water to boiling.
Add gelatins and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 16 individual molds or two 1-quart molds.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese chuck roast
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Cut roast into chunks.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain fat from meat. Add potatoes and carrots.
Combine chives and soup.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: Fry meat slowly until brown; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add all ingredients except tomato paste.
Simmer 10 minutes more.
Add paste to which 1 cup hot water has been added.
Mix well; simmer at least 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Salt and flour pork chops; fry until brown.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan with a half cup of water.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Mix
milk,
shredded
cheese, pepper and eggs together. Place artichokes
in
prebaked crust.
Pour milk mixture over top of artichokes and sprinkle with parsley.
Add more milk on top
if need
to
cover
artichokes.
Sprinkle
with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° until firmly set, about 25 minutes.

title: chickette pilaf
directions: Melt butter and rice in pan.
Add chickette and cook for 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken, reserving broth.
Discard bay leaf.
Set chicken aside.
Add rice and carrot to broth; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to broth; heat thoroughly.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: catsup
directions: Skin tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Put in a bag and drain off water overnight.
Put pulp through squeez-o.
Add rest of ingredients and boil for 10 minutes.
Put in bottles or jars and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese carrots
directions: Put carrots in buttered baking dish. Pour melted oleo over them. Put crushed crackers on top of mixture and Cheddar cheese over crackers. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven. Makes 1 pie.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix together the milk, sugar and salt.
Crumble yeast into mixture along with the egg and shortening.
Mix in with spoon, then knead in 2 1/2 cups flour.
Let rise.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon in a small bowl and set aside.
Using electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Add flour gradually, mixing until well blended.
Shape dough into a ball and wrap with plastic wrap. Place in refrigerator and chill 30 minutes.
Divide dough ball in half.
Place one portion between 2 pieces of lightly floured waxed paper and roll into a 10-inch square, about 1/8-inch thick.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Cut into five 1/2-inch strips; twist strips, and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Repeat procedure with remaining dough and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: boursin cheese dip or spread
directions: Cream all ingredients until well blended. Great for spread on crackers.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tugboat annies
directions: Cream
together the oleo, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, nuts and peanut butter chips.
Pack in long baking dish that has been
greased.
Bake
at
for 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.
Or can be packed in greased muffin tins to make uniform.

title: potato reuben casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare potato puffs in 3-quart casserole as directed on package.
Stir in sauerkraut and onions.
Spoon half of the potato-sauerkraut mixture into ungreased 2-quart casserole; cover with corned beef and cheese.
Top with remaining potato-sauerkraut mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix oleo, mustard, horseradish and poppy seed together for sauce.
Place sliced ham and Swiss cheese on hamburger buns. Brush over the inside of hamburger bun and ham with sauce.
Add top of bun and brush lightly with sauce.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 13 minutes at 350°.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and dates in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and pecans.
Divide mixture in half. Place in a damp cup towel and roll each half into small logs.
Let cool.
Unwrap and slice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks (well beaten), flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well and add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla; cook at 375° in baked pie shell until meringue is brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; drain and set aside to cool. Save chicken broth. After cooking, remove chicken from bones. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of chicken and then a layer of stuffing; moisten stuffing with broth. In a separate bowl, mix both soups (still condensed) and layer all of it over stuffing. Then add another layer of chicken, then stuffing and moisten stuffing. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yogurt fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add raspberries.
Stir in raspberry yogurt.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix Veg-All, chicken soup, chicken broth and chicken together. Pour into a buttered glass baking dish.
Mix buttermilk, flour and butter.
Spread over top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bo peep's honey drink
directions: Stir honey in 1 tall glass of milk.
Add a touch of nutmeg or cinnamon for a really delicious drink.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add cream cheese and mayo.
Beat with whisk.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour in greased dish or mold.
Coconut may be sprinkled on top or added to mixture.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream powdered sugar and oleo or butter.
Add egg, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Sift together and add flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Refrigerate dough for 2 to 3 hours. Roll out to 3/16-inch thick.
Flour the cookie cutters.
Cut out cookies.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Boil juice, sugar, margarine and flavoring. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: helen's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add shortening and soft margarine. Blend together.
Add water.
Press into ball and roll to fit pie dish. Makes 2 pie shells or 1 double crust pie.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Into the top of a double boiler, put brown sugar, then put in the buttered bread, cut into cubes, about 3/4 of an inch square. Sprinkle with raisins.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter 5 to 7 minutes or until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, stirring until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients and half of bread cubes. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining bread cubes; bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables in order given.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour tomatoes over all.
Sprinkle with tapioca.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch noodle cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in double boiler. Cool slightly and add noodles, marshmallows and walnuts.
Stir gently to coat and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Flavor is best after sitting in the refrigerator for 24 hours. This can be frozen.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Pour oil and milk into a measuring cup (don't stir).
Then pour into flour.
Stir with fork until mixture leaves sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball.

title: mexican soup
directions: Mix together and heat.
Serve with salad.

title: spaghetti with ham (or turkey) primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Steam broccoli.
In a frying pan, saute garlic, mushrooms and bell pepper in olive oil.
After 2 to 3 minutes, add ham.
In small saucepan over medium heat, combine cornstarch with chicken broth; mix until cornstarch dissolves. Reduce heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Toss broccoli, pasta, vegetables, ham and basil.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly with bread mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican beef roll-ups
directions: Heat tortillas by package directions.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and salsa and spread on tortillas.
Arrange roast beef and a lettuce leaf over sauce.
Roll tortillas in a jelly roll fashion.
Secure with a wooden pick.
Slice each roll in half. Serve with additional salsa.
These are also good crisped under broiler, dipped in mustard or your choice of dip.

title: hot fudge pudding(9 servings)
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in the milk and melted shortening. Blend in the chopped nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour the hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom.
Invert squares of pudding on dessert plates. Dip sauce from pan over each, or the entire pudding can be inverted in a deep serving platter.
Serve warm, with or without whipped cream.

title: quick ground meat with green beans(serves 4)
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in enough water to cover.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 40 minutes until string beans are tender.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: quick and easy bourbon barbecue chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours or overnight, turning once.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered, basting every 15 minutes for 1 hour and 15 minutes until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brownie alaska
directions: Prepare brownies according to package in a 13 x 9 pan. Let cool. Slice ice cream in 4 x 4 x 1/4-inch thick squares. Place ice cream over brownies. In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form, then add sugar. Mix until mixture is stiff. Spread mixture over ice cream. Serve immediately or freeze until ready to eat.

title: potato stuffing for fowl or for casserole use
directions: Bake potatoes with skins on until soft for mashing.
Remove skins after cooking and draining.
Mash.
Add stir-fry ingredients (onions, celery, green pepper, parsley flakes, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper).
Mix into mashed potatoes with milk and butter to taste and consistency.
(You may use a little poultry juice to your added milk, etc. for a better taste.)
Put in fowl and/or casserole to bake.
Feast and enjoy.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful into deep fat.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of greased and floured bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and rum in large mixing bowl.
Blend well for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350 F for 60 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out onto foil large enough to cover the cake when glaze cools.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; debone and chip up.
Place in dish.
Pour chicken broth over chicken.
Spread cream of chicken soup over chicken and broth.
Spread vegetables next, if desired.
Mix milk, flour and melted margarine; pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Add 1 gallon of water to prepare Kool-Aid.
Mix in sugar; add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 1 can broth to 1 can of soup; do not dilute soup with water.
Mix all ingredients except margarine together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine over top, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; peel and slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly in skillet; drain onto paper.
Crumble.
Saute onions in bacon fat until golden brown; blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Stir in carefully the potatoes and bacon.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand until ready to serve.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob and add milk, salt and pepper.
Put butter or margarine in a heavy skillet.
When skillet is hot, add corn. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Just before ready to take up, add beaten eggs.
Blend in well.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate topped peanut brittle
directions: Melt chocolate chips in the top of a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water OR in a microwave according to package instructions. Spread melted chocolate over the peanut brittle to coat. Allow chocolate to cool until firm. Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt butter
in pan.
In a bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk. Stir until mixed.
Pour batter over butter in baking dish or pan.
Don't stir. Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar together. Pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes own crust.

title: butterscotch pie(my sister's, annie laurie bell, recipe)
directions: Toss zucchini, lemon juice and dash of salt together.
Mix sugar, cream of tartar, flour, cinnamon and dash of nutmeg in a bowl.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
It will be runny, but that's okay.
Dump the filling into crust and dot with butter. Add the top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook onions and celery in a small amount of oil.
Add beef. Simmer until beef is nearly done.
Add seasonings, salt, pepper, garlic salt, 3 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon molasses, oil from beef, celery, onions and 1/8 teaspoon ginger.
Add water from bean sprouts, chestnuts and pineapple chunks.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add bean sprouts last.
Serve with Chinese noodles on cooked rice.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in large mixing bowl.
Beat well until thick and smooth.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Line bowl or dish with vanilla wafers, then bananas.
Then alternate layers of filling, bananas and wafers until all is used up.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool for 15 minutes. Poke holes through cake with utility fork. Set aside.

title: baked dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; put in casserole dish.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: cake donuts
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla; stir in milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg and add to first mixture. Add enough additional flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with donut cutter and fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixed or powdered sugar.

title: sweet and sour pork roast
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs, oats and apple butter. Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture along with the milk. Beat until blended. Stir in nuts and raisins. Chill well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken, asparagus, rice dinner
directions: In a 10 inch skillet heat butter.
Cook chicken and carrots until chicken is browned and carrots are tender.
Add rice and cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk, soup, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and reduce heat; cook 15 minutes.
Stir.
Add asparagus and cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until rice and asparagus are tender, stirring often.
Garnish with green onions and serve.

title: appetizer
directions: Be sure the cream cheese, butter and sour cream are at room temperature. Beat gradually. Add the sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Pour warm gelatin over hot water.
Add gelatin to cream cheese mixture and mix.
Add the almonds.
Put in 1-quart mold and refrigerate.
Really yummy.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato sponge bread
directions: Pare and boil potatoes.
While hot, mash finely and rub through sieve or colander.
Add the sugar, salt and dissolved yeast cake.
Stir flour into mixture, beating well.
Add more flour to form soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead. Return to bowl.
Cover and let rise overnight.
Form into loaves. Let rise until light and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, cocoa and add milk gradually.
Stir well and microwave 2-3 minutes on high.
Remove, stir well and return to microwave for 4-5 minutes.
Remove, stir well and beat 1/3 of the hot mixture slowly into 3 beaten egg yolks.
Return mixture to remaining chocolate filling and mix well.
Microwave 2 minutes on high.
Remove, stir, add margarine and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue or cool whip.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over Cool Whip and mix well.
Drain oranges and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; rice potatoes.
Mix all ingredients with 4 tablespoons butter, melted.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with the remaining 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Boil ribs, which have been salted, in large pan until very tender.
Remove them from broth and cook the sweet potatoes (small whole ones or quartered larger ones) in the broth until done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter over medium heat.
Cream powdered sugar into peanut butter mixture.
(Add more, if necessary.)
Add Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate at low heat.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and allow to harden on wax paper.
May freeze or refrigerate in closed container.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, bring to boil.
Stir occasionally. Reduce heat and simmer until thick, about 2 hours.

title: sweet 'n spicy sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as a topping for grilled steaks.
Also good for basting steaks while cooking.

title: arroz con leche(rice 'n milk)
directions: Cook the rice in water.
When the rice is soft, add the remaining ingredients.

title: oreo cookie crunch
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Stir in cream cheese and Cool Whip until mixture is smooth.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Put half of the crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining half of crumbs over mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add all wet ingredients, except tea, and mix.
Add tea and fold in blueberries.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan or make into muffins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Add desired amount to hot water or milk. Store in an airtight container.

title: sausage-egg casserole(breakfast casserole)
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain and cool.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Tear bread into small pieces and fold into egg mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: potato omelet
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add potatoes and onions; saute until tender and golden, stirring often.
Add ham and cook a few minutes.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley and reduce heat.
With a spatula, lift egg mixture from edge of pan so uncooked mixture can run down.
When omelet has nearly set, sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler to melt cheese.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana blueberry nut crunch bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour mixture into medium size baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate filling and icing
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Add cream, then cocoa and vanilla.
Mix in electric mixer until smooth.
Spread on layer cake.
Will cover three 9-inch layers and have enough left to cover the sides, making the cake completely covered.

title: raw vegetable dressing
directions: Beat oil, lemon juice and salt until thick.
Add cream, onion and herbs.

title: griddle-grilled chicken and avocado burritos
directions: In a large heavy skillet melt the butter and oil until hot. Add the chicken.
Cook over medium-high heat until golden and cooked, about 10 minutes.
Shred chicken.
Set aside.
Dice the avocados.
Squeeze juice of lime and toss with avocados.
Set aside.
Butter one side of each tortilla.
On a dry, hot griddle or the skillet you cooked the chicken in, heat 1 tortilla at a time.
Heat until just hot and soft.
On the unbuttered side, place one-eighth of the chicken, avocado and cheese.
Sprinkle with salsa and red pepper sauce, if used, according to taste. Fold up one end and roll.
Heat until slightly crispy.
Serve. Repeat with others.

title: fish salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the lettuce, being careful not to break the fish into too small pieces.
Serve on lettuce cups and garnish with sliced eggs.
Serves 6.

title: cherry pie
directions: Pour pie mix in large pie plate.
Pour 1/2 cake mix on top of cherries.
Smooth over and pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: easy cheezy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Wash chicken and place in pan.
Place a slice of cheese on top of chicken.
Spread the cream of chicken soup over the top of each chicken breast.
Top with a layer of Pepperidge Farm stuffing (dry).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: petite crab quiches
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Add flour. Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Press into small muffin tins.
Bake for 5 minutes in a 350° oven. Combine egg, cream, Parmesan cheese, crab meat and salt.
Pour mixture into muffin tins.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: ranch seasoned pretzels
directions: Break pretzels in small pieces.
Spread on cookie sheet. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over pretzels.
Mix thoroughly until all pretzels are coated.
Bake 6 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Bake 3 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Bake 3 minutes. Take out and stir.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer for about 10 minutes until smooth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil sweet potatoes until a fork inserts easily into them.
Put sugar, extracts, and butter in a large bowl. Pour hot water off the potatoes and add cold water.
Peel the potatoes while warm.
Place the potatoes in the bowl with the sugar mixture.
With an electric mixer, mix for about 5 to 6 minutes, rinsing the mixer blades every minute or so to remove the strings from the potatoes.	(This will make a better textured pie.)
Add the milk, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, cornstarch and condensed milk; mix for 2 to 4 minutes more.
Fill the pie shells.	Place pies on a cookie sheet and cook for 50 minutes or until firm.
Let cool and eat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour in pan (8 x 12-inch pan or glass dish).
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: basic campers mix
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats. Store in airtight container.

title: green beans with potato salad
directions: Wash and snip ends of green beans.
Cut into 2-inch lengths. Cook in salted water until tender but crisp.
Drain and cool. Boil potatoes as in potato salad.
Cool and cut in 1-inch cubes.

title: pecan candy
directions: Melt in top of double boiler the first 3 ingredients, then add pecan halves.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper on cookie sheets.
Chill.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt until it spins a long thread.
Add vanilla.
Pour all over popcorn.
Shape into balls.

title: tomato-bacon linguine
directions: Cook, drain and crumble bacon.	Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat from the pan.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Stir in garlic, tomatoes, sugar, tarragon, peppers and salt.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, stir bacon and parsley into sauce.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Put linguine into serving dishes and spoon some sauce over it.
Sprinkle Parmesan over it.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie shell 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Beat eggs, milk and mayo.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Salt and pepper.
Add cheese and ham, bacon or crabmeat.
Onions or green peppers are good also.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Partially cook bacon.
Add celery and onion, and cook until tender but not brown.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add water to the liquid, to make 4 cups.
Add to bacon mixture.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes.
Blend 2 Tbsp. flour with 2 Tbsp. cold water to make a smooth paste.
Stir into chowder; cook and stir mixture until it boils.
Add clams; heat through.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast, salt, sugar and egg and whip with wire whip. Add oil and flour.
If using an electric mixer, it will be less kneading by hand.
When dough is not sticky, oil and let set for about 30 minutes.
Make out into your favorite rolls, buns, etc. Makes good cinnamon rolls.
Can be refrigerated in airtight container for up to 3 days.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream butter, add sugar slowly while beating. Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add molasses, cloves, fruit, then water with soda.
Lastly add flour.
Chill throughly, several hours or overnight.
Shape into small long rolls the length of greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg yolk mixed with 1 Tbsp. milk.
Bake 375° oven until brown, about 15 minutes.
While hot, cut diagonally across roll.

title: mango cobbler
directions: Sift together the Bisquick, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Add egg and milk; beat thoroughly.
Stir in melted margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix thoroughly until smooth. Pour into an 8 x 11-inch pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, place mangos.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to mangos.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon nutmeg, coriander, 1/4 cup sugar (or sweeten to taste) and lemon juice.
Spread mango mixture over Bisquick.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir often.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in greased casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour and pour over pineapple.
Add cheese to mixture. Top with crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix milk, biscuit mix and eggs. Spread sausage in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with biscuit mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: favorite crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high for 5 to 6 hours).

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries; reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and a dash of salt in a saucepan.
Stir in reserved juice from cherries. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add cherries, butter, almond extract and red food coloring.
Pour into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust; trim and flute edges.
Cut several steam vents near center of pie.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes.

title: quick shrimp skillet
directions: Add margarine to heavy skillet or wok; heat to medium high (325°) for 1 minute.
Add onions, celery, carrots, garlic and mushrooms.
Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add ginger, pepper, soy sauce, shrimp and water; stir-fry until shrimp are pink.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: georgia pecan pie(has a delightful maple flavor)
directions: Mix well, adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until pie is set.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar, milk and butter in double boiler; let cool. Add to Cool Whip.
Add pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Mix together in large bowl brown sugar, white sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Blend in shortening; add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder; stir together and mix in oats.
Roll dough into small balls (1-inch diameter).
Roll balls in sugar.
Flatten slightly on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish and make two layers in this order:

title: all things considered meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: new england baked beans(serving size:  8)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Or, add to cold water and boil for two minutes, then soak for one hour.
Simmer beans (only) for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beans.
Add water to cover.
Bake six hours at 250° or use a crock-pot.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; pour over ice cream.
Top with whipped cream and nutmeg.

title: easy peach cake
directions: Melt margarine in cake pan.
Cover bottom of pan with layer of peaches.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over margarine and peaches.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be served with ice cream on top or without.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Bring brown sugar, milk and butter to a boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy, adding a little cream, if necessary, to make easier to spread.
Makes enough for top and sides of 9-inch square cake.

title: garlic corn
directions: Mix and cook.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, add eggs and bananas.
Beat well, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough regular milk to make 4 quarts.
(Chill Eagle Brand milk before using.)

title: sugar-free pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients well.
Chill before serving.
Can be poured into graham cracker pie shell.

title: turnip greens with roots
directions: Wash 2 bunches turnip greens thoroughly.
Chop greens into small pieces.
Put greens in pot with 4 cups water.
More water may be used if necessary.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 pound salt pork.
Chop roots into small pieces.
Bring to brisk boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: black bean soup
directions: In a large pot, cook bacon.
Add onion and saut until golden.
Add celery, carrots and garlic and cook over medium heat until soft, about 15 minutes.
Add beans, chicken broth, water, cumin and salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir frequently to keep beans from sticking.
Add more water if necessary.
Scoop out 1/2 the beans and mash to a paste.
Return to pot.
Add cilantro if desired.
Serve with sour cream, green onions and cheese.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap uncooked bacon slices around water chestnuts; secure with toothpicks.
Place on cookie sheet in a 350° oven.
Cook until transparent.
Heat equal parts of sugar and ketchup (1 cup each) in a saucepan until smooth.
Place wraps and sauce in a baking dish; heat in the oven.

title: broccoli bake from luba
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water briefly to make it crisp and tender; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients except for crackers.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish; top with crackers.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chili my way (quick)
directions: Cook onion and garlic until done, but not brown.
Cook hamburger also.
Add all ingredients and cook for 1 hour or longer, depending on how hungry you are.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat until soft the butter or shortening.
Add gradually and blend until creamy the brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Add all-purpose flour.
Roll the dough into small balls.
Place them on a greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: asparagus fromage
directions: Drain asparagus; reserve 1 cup liquid.
Melt butter.
Add flour slowly.
Add milk and liquid; stir constantly until thick. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until smooth.
Add scrambled eggs. Season to taste.
Pour a layer of sauce in casserole dish.
Add asparagus and pour remaining sauce on top.
Combine cheese, crumbs, parsley and paprika; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and it will be thick. Melt 2 sticks of butter in a 9x13 pan. Pour mixture over the butter and spread out. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first bowl.
Add zucchini and mix together. Bake in 9 x 13 pan or glass dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles half time suggested on package in water, then drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and add noodles.
Pour in greased casserole and bake 1 hour in 350° oven covered.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in casserole dish.
Mix soup and mayonnaise; cover.
Add butter; sprinkle with crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew ala fitz
directions: In a small plastic bag, put flour, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add stew meat; shake to coat well.
In heavy pan, heat oil.
Add meat and brown.
Cook meat at medium-low heat for 30 minutes.
You will need to add water to meat occasionally.
This will make a nice gravy.
Add onion and celery; let cook for another 15 to 20 minutes, adding water as needed.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook until tender, adding water as needed.
Serves 6.

title: sybil's microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass loaf pan, except catsup.
Place in microwave for 10 minutes.
Turn it.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain grease off.
Pour catsup over top and cook 5 more minutes.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Gradually add flour and salt into batter.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet, ungreased.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until edges brown.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix together all wet ingredients, then add the dry ingredients into wet BY HAND (DO NOT USE MIXER).
Then add zucchini, chopped fine and chopped pecans.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
You can also hollow out a loaf of sourdough bread.
Fill the bread bowl with spinach dip and surround it with the bread you hollowed out, cut and torn in pieces.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs with cream, flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg, butter and sherry.
Stir in cheese.
Pour over seafood in shell.
Bake 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
In 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat in hot olive oil, cook chicken a few pieces at a time until browned on all sides; set aside chicken.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut acorn squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out and discard seeds.
Place squash, cut side up, in baking pan.
Fill cavities with dots of butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is transparent.
Blend flour, add milk stirring constantly.
Blend in cheese, salt, pepper, garlic, worcestershire sauce and chicken. Stir until cheese is melted.
Mix sauce and spaghetti.
Place all in a casserole dish, sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with a little minced onion.
Drain.
Add green beans and tomato soup.
Heat until bubbly.

title: creamy peppercorn dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth, adding dill pickle juice to thin to desired consistency.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain about half the liquid from the beans.
Saute bacon, onion and liquid smoke.
Mix the 5 cans of beans together with all other ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jelly(the easy way)
directions: Wash and sterilize jars and lids.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine juice and sugar.
Stir well with a metal spoon.
Add margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in liquid pectin.
Bring to a rolling boil again, stirring constantly, and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; skim foam from the top of the mixture.
Fill the jars to within 1/4 inch of the top.
Wipe the rims and seal.
Turn jars upside-down for 5 minutes, then turn right-side up.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in boiler and cook until potatoes are tender.
Or combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and shredded cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan firmly packed brown sugar, granulated sugar, milk and butter (or margarine).
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring often.
Boil for 15 minutes over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm and cut into squares. Yield:
2 1/2 pounds.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, egg and brown sugar over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and stir until cool, about 5 minutes.
Stir in Rice Krispies and nuts.
With buttered hands roll teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese, margarine and Italian seasoning; spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli rice strata with cashews
directions: Cook brown rice according to package directions.
In large skillet, heat oil and saute onion and garlic with dill, thyme and oregano.
When vegetables are tender, add parsley, mushrooms and green pepper.
Continue cooking for 2 minutes, then stir in broccoli.
Saute until broccoli is crisp-tender. Add nuts and remove from heat.
Spread rice over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with both cheeses and cover with sour cream.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and cheese is melted.

title: frozen fruit cup(salad)
directions: Line a muffin tin with paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients and pour in cups.
Freeze.
Set out to soften before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Put frozen hash browns in skillet.
Melt oleo and pour over potatoes.
Mix sour cream, onion, cheese, soup, salt and pepper. Add to potatoes and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine corn flakes and oleo.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add wine to mushroom soup. Blend.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour (covered).
Remove chicken. Place chicken over rice on a platter.
Take sour cream and blend into pan with chicken "juice".
Stir until it just comes to a boil. Pour over chicken.
Enjoy!

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese sauce, cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Layer cheese mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle black olives evenly.
Drizzle with sour cream and salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn.
Mix with soup, sour cream and onion.
Place in oven casserole dish.
Cover top with Ritz cracker crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Add all ingredients to crushed wafers.
Keep hands dusted with confectioners sugar as you roll dough into balls the size of walnuts, then roll balls in confectioners sugar.

title: green rice
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove very carefully the insides from the tomatoes with a small sharp knife.
Pick out crabmeat; flake in medium-sized bowl.
Mix crabmeat, onion, relish and mayonnaise in a bowl thoroughly. (Note:
More or less mayonnaise can be used.)

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Blend dry ingredients slowly.
Add milk, beating thoroughly.
Blend in vanilla and morsels.
Grease tube pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: swiss cheese tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into 36 balls.
Place each ball into individual well of 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.

title: rosemary potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Pat dry with paper towels; place in an 11 x 7 inch baking dish.
Drizzle with oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary and remaining ingredients; toss well.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
6 servings of 5 wedges. Calories 119.

title: basic chicken broth
directions: Put chicken and water in a stock pot.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and falls away from the bones. Strain.
Remove from the bones (freeze for later use).
Refrigerate broth overnight; fat will float to the top.
Skim and discard the fat.

title: pork chop chasseur
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/2 cup liquid, cut up tomatoes.
In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, reserved tomato liquid, onion, mustard and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes and pickles; heat.
Combine rice and parsley.
Serve chops over rice.

title: english walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and flour sifted with dry ingredients and soda dissolved in 1 tablespoon warm water.
Add dates or raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered tin. Bake to medium brown 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make well in center and add remaining ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten well.
Fill muffin pans 1/2 full. Makes 12 to 16 large muffins. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Grease and dust with flour two 9-inch layer pans.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add butter, shortening, vanilla and buttermilk.
Blend on low speed for about 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for two minutes.
Add egg whites.
Beat for 2 minutes.

title: baked salmon
directions: Rinse steaks thoroughly in cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
Place into a shallow baking pan coated with vegetable cooking spray; brush with lemon juice. Sprinkle evenly with dill weed, parsley and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Make into balls and flatten to bake or roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Ice with Buttercream Icing.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; put into a casserole dish and sprinkle rice over hamburger.
Heat soup and water; pour over hamburger-rice. Bake 1 hour at 245°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken, carrot, onion and celery in salted water for 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain, skin and bone chicken.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Grease a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Arrange broccoli and top with chicken.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Trim vegetables in bite size pieces and toss with pimentos, onion and bell pepper.

title: cold pineapple chiffon cake
directions: Mix pineapple, lemon juice and pudding.
Beat whipping cream until milky; mix with pudding mixture.
Cut cake into 4 layers. Spread pudding mixture on all cake layers.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Combine Oreos and melted margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Mix in 6 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread on Oreo crust.
Refrigerate.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with 10 ounces Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Note:
Can substitute 3 cups berries, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cornstarch.
Cook in saucepan until thick.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Work together powdered sugar, margarine, vanilla and peanut butter with hands until well blended.
Roll into balls.
Chill slightly.
Place each on fork and dip in melted chocolate.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix all together.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: gramma's date bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with fingers.
Slice dates into fourths.
Add to water and sugar in pot and boil 1/2 hour.
Let stand to cool.
Spread 1/2 of oat mixture in baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Spread on dates and top with remaining oat mixture. Press down firmly.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter crisscross
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and mix well.
Blend in all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten crisscross style with fork dipped in flour or water.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients for batter together.
Bake in cake pans until cooked through.
Put topping between layers.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar mixture.
Place loosely in a greased tube pan.
To remaining sugar mixture, add 1 tablespoon water.
Melt margarine and sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Cut into cubes the Mozzarella cheese.
Shape meatball mixture around each cube of cheese.
Coat each meatball with flour and brown in 2 teaspoons vegetable or salad oil until done.
Drain off fat and add pizza sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Allow to marinate until serving time. Keep hot.
Serve over cooked rice or in bread pita pockets or hot dog buns.
These freeze and reheat well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and combine other ingredients.
Pour in casserole and pour corn over.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat spinach-stuffed flounder
directions: Rinse flounder.
Cook spinach until tender.
Drain water well. Set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix into spinach.
Add breadcrumbs.
Lay fish flat; place spinach mixture in center.
Roll sides under and place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Squeeze on fresh lemon and garnish with parsley before serving.
Serves 4.

title: creamy taters
directions: Mix sour cream and soups together thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Fold in frozen potatoes.
Spread mixture evenly into a 9X13 pan coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: healthy snack
directions: Place celery, carrots and cheese on a plate and dressing in a bowl.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients and the onion.
Break in the egg and beat vigorously.
Add the milk; stir together.
Make small round cakes, 2 inches in diameter.
Poke a hole in the center with finger, a doughnut.
Slide into deep fat in which fish has been fried, until they are deep brown.
Serve hot and at once.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: caramel-pecan french silk pie
directions: Prepare and bake pie crust.
Set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, combine 1 cup whipping cream, chocolate, butter and sugar.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir half of the hot mixture into beaten yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat for 5 minutes or until it begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
(Mixture may appear to separate.)
Stir in creme de cacao or whipping cream.
Place saucepan in bowl of ice water for about 20 minutes or until mixture stiffens and is difficult to stir.
Transfer chocolate mixture to a medium mixing bowl.
Beat cooled chocolate mixture with an electric mixer for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Spread caramel topping in bottom of pie crust.
Sprinkle nuts over caramel.
Carefully spread filling into crust.
Cover and refrigerate a minimum of 5 hours. To serve, top with whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups together.
Mix rice with soup.
If thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup milk.
Put into casserole dish.
Lay seasoned chicken parts on top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: honey-grilled tenderloins
directions: Make a lengthwise cut down center of each tenderloin to within 1/4-inch of opposite side; press to open. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger in a shallow dish. Add tenderloins. Cover or seal and chill 3 hours, turning occasionally. Stir together brown sugar, honey and oil.
