Grill tenderloins covered with grill lid over medium-high heat (350° to 400°) 20 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted into thickest portion registers 160°, turning occasionally and basting with honey mixture. Yield: 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add corn and stir.
Beat eggs, milk and butter; stir well.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.
Great dish to take to any gathering.
Triple the recipe and it will make a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Always popular!

title: smokey macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Shred smoked Cheddar cheese (about 3/4); set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients except eggs.
Cool mixture.
Combine yeast, shortening mixture and eggs.
Put electric beater on slow and gradually add 3 cups flour.
Remove beater and beat by hand.
Add 1 1/2 cups to 2 cups more flour to make a soft dough.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator.
When ready to use, break off needed dough and make into rolls.
Let rolls rise for 3 hours, until double in size.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until brown. Makes at least 3 dozen rolls.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and catsup in bowl. Add shrimp.
Refrigerate.
Remove 15 minutes before serving. Serve with Bugles snacks.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Melt margarine over low flame; add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix in cornflakes well until coated.
Drop on wax paper and shape.
Decorate with red hots.

title: jello prehistoric pudding
directions: Crush cookies in a food processor or in zipper-style plastic bag with a rolling pin.

title: peter pan peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Shape 1 teaspoon of dough.
Press into slim "S" shape and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Insert peanut in end of dough.
Press dough with back of floured fork to make crisscross.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, saltines, egg, onion, garlic salt, celery flakes and ketchup all together.
Roll into balls.
Brown in skillet. Remove from skillet.
Put in large pan.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: cocoa gravy and biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in medium skillet.
Add cocoa mixture.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk to thin, if needed.
Serve over buttered biscuits.
Kids love these.
Just make sure to prepare plenty.
Makes enough for about 8 large biscuits.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, and cheese until soft dough forms.	Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.	Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Mix margarine with garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.	Serves 4-6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in seasoned water until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into small pieces.
Heat together soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for 5 minutes.
Top each tortilla with chicken and 2 tablespoons soup mixture.
Roll up.
Continue this procedure for all tortillas.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture over enchiladas.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: shrimp dip for veggies
directions: Drain shrimp and put in ice water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with your favorite veggies.

title: oriental cabbage
directions: Combine margarine and vegetables in a large skillet or electric skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Stir in milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: honey orange rolls
directions: Combine the mixture and mix well all the ingredients except the biscuits.
Separate
the biscuits and put in a Bundt pan. Layer the mixture and biscuits.
Be sure to grease the Bundt pan. Bake in oven at 400° for 16 to 22 minutes.

title: pizza rice
directions: In a slow cooker combine rice, sauce, water, mushrooms and pepper. Stir. Cover and cook on high 6 hours. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, water, onion and seasoning. Add chicken, carrots, peas and potatoes. Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: grampa's concoction
directions: Peel onions and slice thin.
Slice the green peppers thin. Saute in butter. Add drained potatoes.
Add pork and beans.
Slice hot dogs and add to mixture.
Heat thoroughly and serve. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: mother's best gingerbread
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar;
add beaten egg and molasses, then
dry
ingredients, which have been sifted together. Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
The batter is soft, but makes a fine cake.
Bake in greased shallow pan 35 minutes in
moderate oven, 325° to 350°.
Makes 15 generous portions. Good ole fashioned gingerbread.

title: spring salad
directions: Chop and mix vegetables.
Pour lemon juice over vegetables and place in refrigerator to stay cool until ready to serve.
Salt and add oil.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup. Put in a loaf pan. Refrigerate overnight. Slice before cooking.
Roll slices in flour and brown on both sides. Put in a baking dish and pour soup over slices.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain.
Mix the meat, soups, taco sauce and chiles.
Line a greased pan with Doritos, alternating layers of meat sauce and Doritos.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sausage and linguini italiano
directions: Cook and stir celery, onion and garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cook slowly 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve water, marshmallows, lime jello and cream cheese over low heat, then add milk, pineapple, mayonnaise and pecans.
Before adding last 4 ingredients, remove from heat.
Pour into shallow dish and chill.

title: chicken provencal(the oregonian)
directions: In a large Ziploc bag, combine chicken, thyme, rosemary, salt, garlic, sun-dried tomatoes, pepper, oil, mushrooms, sugar, vinegar, olives and capers; toss to blend well.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 12 hours.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Combine ingredients and put into a greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: fried frog legs
directions: The only place you can find alligator is near the coast or the inland swamps in
the South.
So if you're lucky enough to get a holt to an	alligator tail, there's a section about a foot long just behind the
back
legs that's tender and juicy. You cut it in sections at
the
joints
just
like you would a pork chop.
Salt, pepper and flour each piece of tail and then fry in hot grease until
golden brown.
Or you can barbecue it with Bosie's Barbecue Sauce.
He had alligator tail especially in mind when
he concocted
it.
If	you haven't eaten 'gator tail before, you're in	for
a	surprise.
It's gonna taste a little bit like chicken, a little bit like pork, and a little bit like fish.
It's so good you'll wanna lay down and scream.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine cottage cheese, parmesan cheese and egg. Mix well. On bottom of a 15 x 9 greased baking dish, spread 1 C pasta sauce. Top with half each of the uncooked noodles, cottage cheese mixture, sausage, remaining pasta sauce and mozzarella. Repeat layering. Cover tightly. Bake 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: turtle cake(also called snickers cake)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
For variation, potatoes may be baked in unbaked pie shell and topped with marshmallows or other toppings.

title: broccoli with garlic cheese sauce
directions: Clean and steam broccoli to taste.
While broccoli is steaming, saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Add soup and cheese and melt slowly over low heat so it does not stick.
Pour over the steamed broccoli and serve.
Very good!

title: salsa beef
directions: Brown beef in skillet in oil. Place in slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients. Cover. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve over rice.

title: buttercream icing(like they use for wedding cakes.)
directions: Beat about 5 minutes.
May be necessary to thin.

title: golden baked onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart shallow oval baking dish.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until tender and translucent, stirring frequently, for about 15 minutes.
Transfer onions to dish.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour over onions.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Dip bread in melted butter on one side.
Arrange buttered side up over onion mixture to cover completely.
Bake until bread is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: fried artichokes
directions: Use very small artichokes;
the heart shouldn't be more than an
inch
in diameter.
Peel them.
Take all outer leaves off until
you
have
tender leaves.
Cut off the prickly top. Parboil in
salt and water for 15 minutes.
Drain, standing on leaf end so all water will drain out.
Slice lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Dip in
beaten
egg
and cracker crumbs.
Fry in oil until tender. Serve with mayonnaise.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour Slice or Live Wire into ice cream maker.
Add condensed milk.
Cover.
Put ice and rock salt into maker (alternating) until full.
Let maker run until done.
Refill ice and rock salt as needed.

title: pot pie
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and eggs together.
Add egg and milk mixture to flour mixture. Stir with a fork until dough is of right consistency.
Remove dough from bowl.
Flour dough lightly.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
Cut into small squares and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Boil about 10 minutes, covered.
Add the 1 cup milk and serve.

title: custard
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Set casserole in pan of hot water to bake.

title: dream salad
directions: Cut grapes in half (cherries also).
Put all ingredients, except Dream Whip, in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
(If using Dream Whip, mix in separate bowl according to package directions and pour over ingredients.)
Mix well.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 tablespoons sugar over all.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until combined well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth. Chill several hours before serving.
Keeps for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix cheeses and garlic well.
Shape into two rolls.
Spread nuts on piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle paprika over nuts.
Roll cheese roll over nuts.
Wrap in foil and chill.
Slice to serve with your favorite cracker.

title: the recipe
directions: First layer the ground beef and then the green beans.
Put the mashed potatoes on top of that and bake about 30 minutes in moderate oven as everything has been cooked.

title: guinea grinders
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Cut Vienna bread loaf in half long way. Put ingredients on bottom half of bread section and top with cheese.
Brown under broiler.
Cover with other half of bread section and cut into sections.
Add hot peppers before eating, if preferred.
Serves approximately 4.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring to a boil; cook for 20 minutes.
Add 1/4 stick oleo and 1 cup half and half.
Do not boil.
By the time the margarine is melted, the soup is ready.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Squeeze lemons to get 1/2 cup of juice.
Melt butter and pour with lemon juice over chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Recipe can easily be doubled.

title: tuna rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve. Yields about 10 servings.

title: fudgy no-bake(without peanut butter)
directions: In a pan combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir together well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool or eat warm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in two loaf pans in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Good with Nutmeg Butter.

title: elm cottage pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter.
Add egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to the butter and sugar mixture, half at a time, beating constantly.
Alternating with 1 cup of milk, beat in vanilla.
Bake for 25 minutes in a greased 10-inch square baking pan.
Serve warm from pan.

title: jumbo shells with cheese stuffing
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Combine cheeses, bread crumbs, salt, egg and parsley together.
Fill jumbo shells immediately with cheese mixture, using knife or pastry bag.
Pour half of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange shells on top in single layer.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In one mixing bowl, combine flour, cocoa, sugar, salt and soda; set aside.
In another bowl, mix oil, water, vanilla and vinegar.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and blend well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake no. 3
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar with shortening and margarine; beat in eggs and then sour cream.
Combine flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings. Bake 1 1/2 hours in cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam or other vegetable spray.
Absolutely great tasting!
Yields 24 servings.

title: angel food cake trifle
directions: Prepare angel food cake according to directions on box.
Let cool and cut into small squares.
Alternate layers of cake, and all fruits, pouring a little of the fruit juices over each layer. Layer whipped topping between each layer.
After trifle bowl is full, spread whipped topping over entire top and decorate with extra sliced fruits.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Blend all ingredients into beaten eggs.
Pour into greased Pyrex pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening or oleo, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.

Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Line with cookie dough, patted to fit pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat milk and water.
Stir in onions, celery, butter, salt, pepper, sauce and flakes.
Heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat cooked beets in double boiler.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add vinegar and juice.
Pour over beets; add butter.
Stir occasionally until mixture gets thick.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat in bananas. Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or spread with whipped cream while warm.

title: cranberry roast pork
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: berry pudding
directions: Cream
the
butter and sugar;
add the yolk (well beaten). Add
alternately
the
flour
sifted
with	salt, baking powder and
a
grating
of
nutmeg and the milk.
Fold in the whites of egg beaten stiff and the berries dredged with flour. Bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: applesauce drop doughnuts
directions: Combine first 4 items in bowl at medium speed.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients, add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in applesauce and vanilla.
Pour 2 to 3 inches of oil in saucepan.
Heat at 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoon. Cook 2 minutes each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: strawberry nut loaf
directions: Thaw strawberries about halfway.
Combine first 3 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In a separate smaller bowl, sift together dry ingredients and stir into strawberry mixture until thoroughly blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into two 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake in (preheated) 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in sugar and flour until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk; add eggs and baking powder.
Mix well with milk. Turn into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour into a baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together; form into tiny balls. Brown and drain.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until melted. Add meatballs; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: goof-proof p-nut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 1 minute.
(Do not stir during boiling.) Remove from stove and beat the 10 crushed soda crackers, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust (prick it).
Cook bacon; crumble when drained.
Mix together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Put bacon in pie crust.
Layer in Swiss cheese.
Pour on milk mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread.
Stir in brown sugar and raisins.
Pour mixture into 8 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Place pan in large shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water in large shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cut
butter and cheese into small pieces.
Cook spinach and drain.
Beat
eggs	well.
Stir
cottage
cheese,
flour, butter, cheese and spinach into eggs.
Grease dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in large heavy pan on high heat. Cook until peanuts parch and syrup will spin a web.
Remove from burner and add oleo and vanilla; let oleo melt.
Add baking soda and rapidly stir into mixture.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and let cool, until cool enough to break.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix pretzels
and oleo and bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool. Combine
cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over cold crust.
Mix jello, water and strawberries and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken luau foil dinner
directions: Place
chicken	in
foil.
Add pineapple slices, tomato and potato
slices.
Add barbecue sauce and seal.
Cook on bed of coals
for	45 minutes.
Check if meat is still pink.
Cook for another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jane's date bars
directions: Put chopped dates in 1/4 cup of flour to prevent sticking; chopped, square dates work well.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
With your mixer, place all ingredients in the bowl and beat until it resembles a muffin mix. Spoon into a lightly buttered and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: energy bars
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in oven for 5 minutes.
Melt next 3 ingredients.
Mix the dry ingredients with the melted ingredients. Cool and cut into bar size.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13 cake pan.
While warm, spoon pineapple and juice over cake.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nuts and cherries over top. Chill.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Can place a red or green cherry on top.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour. Mix well and add chopped nuts.
Form small balls 1 1/2-inches long. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately browned.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes three dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into large cubes.
In a 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water and salt.
Boil until tender, but firm, about 20 minutes.
While potatoes are cooking, peel eggs.
Finely dice 3 eggs into small pieces in medium mixing bowl. Add pickles, mayonnaise, salt and onion.
Mix well.
When potatoes are done, drain well and put back into saucepan.
Pour egg mixture over potatoes and toss lightly until coated well. (More mayonnaise may be needed.
If so , add now.)
Spoon into serving dish.
Garnish with 1 sliced egg, paprika and parsley, if desired.
Delicious served warm.

title: amy's cheese dip
directions: Soften Cheddar spread and cream cheese at room temperature. Cream together with mixer until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
A good veggie dip!

title: 11 layer salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer each ingredient as it is listed in order, ending with cheese.
Cover and chill.
This is best made ahead and chilled overnight.
Serve with favorite salad dressing.

title: easy baked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash fish in cold water.
Pat dry. Spread mayonnaise over each side of the fish and roll in crushed Ritz crackers.
Place in flat shallow pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish is white and flaky.

title: health salad
directions: In large bowl, toss together cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Stir together vinegar, corn oil, sugar, celery seed and garlic salt.
Pour over vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: rainbow raspberry surprise cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs.
Blend to moisten ingredients, then beat at medium speed for two minutes, until mixture is creamy.
Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Spoon 1/3 of the batter into pan.
Sprinkle with half of the raspberry gelatin.
Repeat layers.
Spread the rest of the batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Let the cake cool in the pan for 5 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and finish cooling on a rack.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge drops
directions: Combine the chocolate and butterscotch chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until smooth and melted.
Remove from heat and stir in cereal and nuts.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma took's cinnamon fingers
directions: Toast bread.
Spread with butter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; mix well.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on buttered toast.
Cut toast into strips.
Serve with a kiss.

title: fruit delight pie
directions: Prepare whipped dessert topping according to package directions.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and vanilla smooth.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and oleo together.
Roll into balls and refrigerate for one hour.
Melt 2/3 bar paraffin wax with the chocolate chips.
Dip cookies in chocolate with spoon and set to dry on wax paper.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Tear chicken or turkey in bite size pieces and place in ungreased casserole dish.
Pour drained can of Veg-All over chicken pieces.
Combine 1 cup of the milk and can of soup in small bowl and pour over mixed vegetables. Use same bowl to melt stick of oleo.
Add remaining cup of milk and stir in Bisquick mix.
Pour over vegetable and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread onto baked crescent rolls.
Top with veggies and cheeses.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: easy brown rice
directions: Brown rice in a skillet with 1/2 stick margarine.
Remove from heat and add onion soup, consomme and mushrooms.
Pour into rectangular baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: elderberry wine
directions: Mash ripe berries and let stand 8 days, stirring well each day. Strain.
Combine water, sugar and 1 quart of berry juice.
Allow to ferment in a warm place.
Then seal.

title: refrigerator nut cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Gradually add to mixture.
Add nuts to flour mixture if you use them.
Shape into 2 or 3 long rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Can be frozen and used one at a time.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Stir to mix.
Combine margarine, fructose, egg and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat in sweetener of your choice.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Beat until blended.
Meanwhile, combine oatmeal and raisins in a bowl. Work with your fingers or a spoon to separate the raisins and coat them with the oatmeal.
Beat into cookie mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° (190°C) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet, then move to cooling rack.

title: rice cheese pie dessert
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan (this will be full to brim).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla nut fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan until smooth.
Cook and stir to a full all-over boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; beat until candy is thick and loses its shine.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 21 pieces.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Lay chicken in mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Turn oven on to 350° and place long casserole dish in oven with margarine until margarine melts.
Meanwhile, remove skin from chicken and lightly flour.
Remove dish from oven and swirl margarine around dish.
Place chicken in dish, skin side down. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: deluxe fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 275°. Line with brown paper 2 loaf pans (size 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4). Mix oil, brown sugar and egg. Beat vigorously with a spoon or mixer for 2 minutes. Sift together flour and spices. Stir into oil mixture alternately with fruit juice. Mix the 1 cup flour with the fruit and nuts. Pour batter over fruit, mixing thoroughly. Pour into pans. Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours. After baking, let stand 15 minutes before taking from pans. Cool thoroughly on racks before removing paper. Store by wrapping tightly in aluminum foil. Place in a covered container in a cool place to ripen. After cake has been cut, store in the refrigerator.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit 2 hours before serving.

title: great grandma's banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add bananas and mix into batter.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour. Stir in sour milk.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, sugar and nutmeats.
Add oil, eggs and strawberries.
Mix well.

title: speedy yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cup flour, sugar, soda, salt and yeast.
Combine buttermilk, water and margarine.
Heat to 120°.
Stir well and add to dry ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of mixer for 4 minutes. Gradually add rest of flour.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Let rise in a greased bowl until doubled.
Punch down, roll out and cut.
Put in a greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: I cut up and cook enough potatoes, I don't know, maybe 6 to 8 large.
After cooked, mash and fix with milk, butter, salt and pepper as you would if you were serving in a plate, only you put into an unbaked pie crust.
Then top with the other crust.
Put slits in top crust, then pat with milk and bake 10 minutes at 425°, then at 350° until done (when crust is golden).

title: potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan or cooking pot.
Add onion and celery; saute, then add peeled potatoes, cut into bite sized pieces.
Add carrot (about 2 tablespoons).
Cover with water; add salt and bring to boil.
Turn heat to medium and cover.
Cook 20 or 30 minutes, until potatoes are done.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Cook together cornstarch, sugar, water and salt until thick and clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture over egg whites.
Beat 5 minutes.
Place on top of pie or dessert.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken in a pressure cooker.	Remove skin and bones from the meat.
Place the
chicken	in
the
bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour cream
over
chicken,
then add cream of chicken soup. Combine egg,
onion and broth from chicken with dressing mix and spread on top.
Bake
at
350° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In a well-greased casserole, sprinkle the rice.
Add the uncooked ground meat, then sprinkle onion soup on top.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and water mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Crush potato chips; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hazelnut loaf cake
directions: Grease a 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add hazelnuts.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Fold into mixture; mix thoroughly. Stir in brandy.
Put batter into the greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or test with a wooden pick.
Remove from pan and cool. Sift powdered sugar over cooled cake.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Bring water to a boil; add dry ingredients, then slowly add egg and then butter last.
Mix together good until thickened and glossy.
When you don't have an appetite, this will bring it back to you.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix together walnuts, flour and oleo.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: four hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a roasting pan. Bake at 250 degrees for at least 4 hours, the longer the better.

title: sweet and zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; brush on pieces of meat several times during last 15 minutes of grilling time.

title: creamy chicken breast
directions: Arrange 4 whole chicken breasts (boneless and skinless) in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 8 slices of Swiss or Mozzarella cheese.
Combine chicken soup with wine or milk.
Spoon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with 1 cup stuffing mix over all.
Drizzle the melted butter or oleo over stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Spray Pam in loaf pan. Put mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: For topper reserve 1 cup of corn chips.
Combine rest of chips with 1 cup shredded sharp American cheese, chili with beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and minced onion.
Pour into 11x7x1-1/2 baking dish.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or till hot in 375° oven.	Spread top with 1 cup sour cream.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded sharp American cheese.
Circle rest of corn chips around edge.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: baked alaska
directions: On a board, place a layer of sponge cake; lay on vanilla ice cream.
On top place a dry, well beaten mixture of egg whites and powdered sugar.
Brown in hot oven for a moment and serve immediately.

title: my mom's impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Melt oleo and add egg mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Mix together with sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
(Mom used diluted canned Carnation milk.)
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased pie pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 40 minutes or until brown.
This pie makes its own crust and seems to taste better the second day!

title: cheesy taco dip
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage together and drain.
Add taco seasoning and set aside.
In large pan, melt Velveeta and cream cheese with a little milk.
Add soup (do not dilute).
Mix salsa with meat and add to cheese mixture.
Serve over tortilla chips and garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy beef dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and cook 3 hours or longer at 250°.
Good for crock-pot.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blackberry dooby
directions: Bring blackberries to boil in 2 cups of water; let boil about 10 minutes.
Strain blackberries in colander to strain seeds. Combine blackberries and all ingredients, except biscuits, in pot. Cook on medium heat until boiling; let boil 10 minutes.
Pinch off biscuits and drop into mixture to make dumplings (use at least 4 biscuits).
Cook additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix white cake mix according to directions. Put 1/2 of mix in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle a layer of brown sugar over the mix; pour on remaining mix and another layer of brown sugar. Bake as directed on cake mix box.

title: shoo fly pie
directions: Stir soda into boiling water. Add syrup/molasses. Stir well. Stir in beaten eggs. Then add crumbs. It will be lumpy. Do not stir until smooth. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and top with crumbs that were set aside. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Then reduce to 350° and bake another 25 to 30 minutes. Yields two 8 or 9-inch pies.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together; add sugar. Beat all ingredients except nuts and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nuts and coconuts on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple betty
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples. Toss with lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix in 1/4 cup sugar, dried apples and pecans.
Combine bread and remaining sugar in bowl. Stir in butter.
Spoon half of apple mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with half of bread mixture.
Pour water over all.
Repeat the layering.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.

title: frozen oreo ice cream cake
directions: Mix cookies with 1/4 cup butter; press into bottom of large pan.
Slice ice cream into 1 inch slices (slightly soft).
Place layer on top cookie crust; press firmly.
Sprinkle with peanuts and freeze 2 hours.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and melted butter in pan over low heat.
Cream sugar and softened butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in vanilla.
Combine buttermilk and soda and add to mixture, alternating with flour, beating well after each addition. Stir in candy mixture and nuts.
Pour into a buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Frost with chocolate frosting

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix and spread on cool cake.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mold in Cracker Barrel container coated with margarine.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Bake by package directions in 2 layers.
Split layers in half after cool.

title: momma's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Wash well after soaking.
Wash salt pork in hot water.
In a saucepan with enough water to cover, boil beans slowly with salt pork and red pepper, covered, for 3 hours. Combine brown sugar, chili powder, catsup, onion, mustard and corn syrup.
Combine with bean mixture and pour in a large baking dish. Heat oven to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Chop vegetables finely.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chocolate coconut cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Beat egg and sift flour, soda and salt.
Add chopped chocolate bar and add coconut. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Melt butter in oven.
Flour chicken.
Lay into melted butter, skin side down.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn skin side up.
Mix water (sherry) and 2 cans chicken soup.
Bake at 400° until it bubbles and then reduce heat to 350° for 1 hour, or bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add carrots and onion and saute until tender.
Blend in flour, then add broth and milk and cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
Cool and remove from pan.
Cut cake lengthwise to make 2 layers.
Place bottom layer back in pan.
Cut ice cream into even slices and place over bottom layer, using all of ice cream.
Place remaining layer on top.
Cover and freeze.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour batter into a funnel.
Release batter in swirls in 375° oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Dip in sugar. Delicious snack!

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Drop small teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet tin and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 340° oven.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate at least 12 hours before serving.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: fruit shake
directions: Place all ingredients into blender and chop on chop setting, then put blender on mix or puree setting for a few seconds.
It is now ready to drink.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender. Put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling in pan and spread.
Pour pineapple and spread.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Pour on melted butter.
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts over melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious quick waffles
directions: Heat waffle baker on medium.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and cooking oil to eggs.
Add flour mixture and blend until smooth.
Yield: 4 waffles.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Grind cranberries, apple and orange.
Mix in pineapple, sugar and pecans.
Mix jello as directed and add other ingredients. Pour into mold and refrigerate for several hours.

title: hurry up fruit salad
directions: Open and drain cans of pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Peel and slice bananas.
Chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients in a serving bowl.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy breakfast quiche
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls. Cook sausage; drain. Sprinkle over crescent rolls. Next sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese plus grated Cheddar cheese. Mix milk and eggs plus salt and pepper to taste. Pour over entire mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 450° or until done.

title: apricot bavarian cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups apricot nectar.
Add sugar and salt; bring to a boil.
Add remaining nectar and lemon juice. Allow mixture to cool down to room temperature, then fold in egg white.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Beat with electric beater on high speed for 6 to 8 minutes or until fluffy. Fold in whipped topping and pour into an 8-cup mold.
Makes 8 servings.
